Commentary.Commentary: We are back! Indian players stride out to the middle. Dean Elgar and Aiden Markram are the openers for South Africa. Jasprit Bumrah has the ball in hand. Three slips, a gully and a leg gully in place for him. Here we go...
... Second innings ...

Wanderers is always a tricky pitch for the batters around the world and Indians were on the receiving end today. After a solid opening stand between Rahul and Mayank Agarwal, things went down hill for the visitors after Mayank Agarwal's departure. The experienced duo of Pujara and Rahane departed cheaply yet again and though Vihari and Pant had a decent start to their innings they failed to kick on. KL Rahul was again the man for India as he looked a class apart from others but felt soon after a fighting fifty. In the end, the tricky nature of the pitch was too much for the Indian lower order to deal with but they still managed to cross 200 with useful contribution from Ashwin in the end. The pitch has enough help for the bowlers and Indian bowlers will be looking to make full use of it as they have just 202 on the board this time. Can South African openers survive a tricky phase before the end of the play today? Do join us shortly as we wait for the reply.

This is a strong South African bowling attack and they showed it throughout the day despite starting off in a rather rusty fashion. The young pacer Jansen provided the first breakthrough and it was Duanne Olivier, the comeback man who broke the backbone of the Indian middle-order by dismissing both Pujara and Rahane off the consecutive balls. After that, all the bowlers came into their groove and chipped away with wickets at regular intervals. The youngster Jansen picked four wickets but a special mention should go to Lungi Ngidi who went wicketless but was one of the first bowlers to set the tone for South Africa in the morning.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Kagiso Rabada ends India's innings. He bags his third wicket with this one. Bowls a length ball, down the leg side. Mohammed Siraj looks to glance it away but gets a faint edge. Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps pouches it with ease. INDIA BOWLED OUT FOR 202.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Fuller, on middle. Jasprit Bumrah defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, on leg. Jasprit Bumrah swings across the line and gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller, outside off. Pushed towards covers. The batters decide against the single at first but takes it eventually.
Length ball on leg. Mohammed Siraj turns this on the leg side.
On a length, outside off. Mohammed Siraj looks to drive but gets beaten.
Fuller in length, outside off. Mohammed Siraj looks to drive but gets an outside edge. The ball falls just short of the third slip fielder.
Short ball, on middle. Jasprit Bumrah steps put and looks to pull but misses.
FOUR! Kagiso Rabada was searching for a yorker but bowls a full toss, on middle. Jasprit Bumrah takes the advantage and puts it away to long on for a boundary.
Back of a length, outside off. Jasprit Bumrah has a wild swing at it but misses.
SIX! BOOM! Short ball, on middle and leg. Jasprit Bumrah pulls but closes his eyes as the ball approaches. He still manages to clear deep square leg and gets a maximum.
Short of a length, on off. Jasprit Bumrah looks to heave it away but only connects thin air around him.
FOUR! Crucial runs for India! Fuller and on leg. Jasprit Bumrah clears his front leg and flicks it to deep square leg. Gets off the mark with a boundary.
On a good length, on middle. Mohammed Siraj blocks it out on the leg side.

OUT! CAUGHT! Marco Jansen gets another one and Ravichandran Ashwin departs after a valuable innings! Jansen has been the pick of the bowlers and he sends back the dangerous Ashwin back to the pavilion now. A short ball from 'round the wicket outside on middle and leg. Ashwin makes room and looks to upper cut it but gets a top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards gully and Keegan Petersen there takes a fine catch. Just a wicket away now South Africa and they will be looking to get it as early as possible. Mohammed Siraj is the last batter to come in.
Commentary.Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: DROPPED! Will be a bit harsh though to count that as a drop. Length ball, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin makes room and plays an inside out shot. He lifts it towards deep cover. Temba Bavuma sprints to his right and puts in a dive to take the catch. He did held so but then hit the pitch and the ball popped out of his hands. Quite an attempt though. The batters run two.
Good short ball, on leg. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to pull but misses.
Ashwin has been hit on his finger by Jansen! He is getting some treatment now and looks fine to continue. Those are very important fingers for India and luckily they seems good now.
Good-length ball, coming back in, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin gets his bat down in time to defend it out. Looks like that hit his index finger and he looks in some pain.
OUT! CAUGHT! Marco Jansen gets another one!
Another good-length delivery, seaming away from outside off. Bumrah lets it go this time.
A good-length delivery outside off. Bumrah makes room and has a slash at it but misses.

That took off after landing! A top-nut from Kagiso Rabada. Good-length ball, outside off. The ball shoots up after hitting the deck. Jasprit Bumrah is taken aback by the bounce and leaves it untouched. He can only afford a smile there.
Jasprit Bumrah is the new batsman in.

OUT! CAUGHT and BOWLED! That's a sharp catch from Rabada! India re eight down now. A handy little partnership comes to an end. A full ball on from Rabada. Shami hits this hard just left of Rabada. He is quick to judge the pace of the ball and pouches it with both hands. Second wicket for Rabada and good and South Africa will be looking to bundle out India under 200 here. Can India get another partnership going and cross that 200 mark?
Commentary.Howout: c & b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, on off. Shami pushes it towards covers.
A fuller ball by Rabada this time on middle. Shami comfortably pushes it to mid on.
NO BALL! Overstepping by Rabada! A length ball, on middle. Ashwin works it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Back of  a length, on middle. Aswin works it to mid-wicket and gets a single to retain the strike.

Short and wide again. Shami slashes this hard through point this time. Temba Bavuma gives it a chase and cuts it off near the fence by stopping the ball with his foot. Three runs taken by the batters.
FOUR! Go big or go home approach by Shami! These are crucial runs for India. Short and wide outside off. Shami slashes it hard and gets it over the slip corridor for a boundary.
Back of a length on middle. Shami awkwardly defends it towards leg gully.
Short ball this time on middle. Ashwin pulls it to fine leg for a  single.
FOUR! This has been a good counter-attacking innings from Ashwin here! A length ball, on off. Ashwin just lifts this over mid on for a boundary. He is getting crucial runs for India here.
Back of a length on middle. Ashwin works it towards the on side and gets a single.
A full ball, on middle again. Ashwin pushes it to mid on this time.
FOUR! Superb timing by Ashwin again! A full ball, on the pads. Ashwin flicks it aerially towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.

A length ball and nipping into the batter. Shami looks to clip it but misses. The ball hits his pads and goes towards fine leg. There is a loud appeal but the umpire is unmoved and South Africa decides against the review. A leg bye taken.
Another back-of-a-length delivery outside off. Shami plays it away from the body and the ball beats the outside edge of his blade.
Back of a length, on off. Shami defends it awkwardly towards the on side.
Uppish but safe! Length ball, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin chips it to deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs. Hands over the strike to Mohammed Shami for the next over.
Length ball, on off. Ravichandran Ashwin covers the line and defends it well.
Short ball from Olivier now, down leg. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to pull but fails to connect.
Outside off, on a length. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes it to the off side.
On a length, on off. Ravichandran Ashwin defends it out.
Outside off, on a length. Ravichandran Ashwin lets it sail through.
On a length, outside off. Mohammed Shami drives it through covers for a couple of runs.
Short of a length, outside off. Mohammed Shami has a slash at it but misses. Shami needs to be more careful here. Every run from here on can prove vital from india's point of view.
Good-length ball, on middle. Mohammed Shami looks to push but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller in length, on off. Ravichandran Ashwin lifts it straight over the bowler's head for three runs.
Back of a length, outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin taps it to point.
Good-length ball, on off. Ravichandran Ashwin defends it from the crease.
Mohammed Shami is the next batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT! Duanne Olivier bags his third wicket now. A nothing shot from Shardul Thakur. Back of a length, outside off. Shardul Thakur hangs back and dabs this one towards gully. Keegan Petersen there takes a dolly. Two wickets in two overs for South Africa and India lose their seventh wicket. Can they restrict India under 200?
Commentary.Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Duanne Olivier

Commentary.Commentary: In the air, but safe! Length ball, on off. Shardul Thakur chips it towards short extra cover. The ball falls jsut short of him.
Short again, on middle. Shardul Thakur looks to pull as well but the ball goes past him in a jiffy.
Short and on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin pulls it without any timing to deep square leg for a run.
On a length, on off. Defended out.
Good-length ball, on off. Pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball, on middle. Shardul Thakur turns this to short leg.
Back of a length, on off. Shardul Thakur hops and blocks it from the crease.
Shardul Thakur is the next batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Marco Jansen strikes once again and India in deep trouble now. An inswinger, this time, around off. Rishabh Pant presses forward to defend. The little inward movement of the ball takes the inside edge and carries through to the keeper. Kyle Verreynne does really well to dive to his right and catch the ball. Rishabh Pant is on his way to the pavilion. Once again just when there was a partnership building, South Africa have struck and are into India's lower order.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Fullish, outside off. An outswinger but too wide. Left alone.
On a length, on middle. Ravichandran Ashwin flicks it to deep square leg. He crosses ends.
Fuller, outside off. Driven towards covers.
On the pads, Rishabh Pant clips it on the leg side.
Outside off, Rishabh Pant shoulders arms.
On a good length, on off. Rishabh Pant taps it towards covers. He looks for a quick single but is sent back by Ravichandran Ashwin and rightly so.
Short and on leg, Ravichandran Ashwin pulls it to deep square leg for a run.
Fuller, on middle. Ashwin pushes it to mid on.
FOUR BYES! A loosener from Duanne Olivier, down the leg side. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to pull but misses. The keeper fails to collect the ball and it rolls to fine leg for four byes.
Duanne Olivier to start from the other end.
Full and on off. Rishabh Pant strokes this one behind backward point for another brace.
Short ball, on off. Rishabh Pant pulls it towards deep square leg. Kagiso Rabada from fine leg runs to his right and dives to stop the ball. Does well to keep it down to two.
Fuller, outside off, swinging away. Rishabh Pant offers no shot.
Close leave! Good-length ball, around off. Rishabh Pant watches the ball sail past him. The ball was inches away from hitting the off stump.
Length ball, outside off. Rishabh Pant shoulders arms.
Length ball, on off. Rishabh Pant covers the line and defends it back to the bowler.

We are back for the final session of Day 1! South African players stride out to the middle. Ravichandran Ashwin and Rishabh Pant are also their in the middle to resume their innings. Marco Jansen to start with the ball for South Africa.
... DAY 1, SESSION 3 ...

The stand-in captain, KL Rahul did a solid job and led from the front where others struggled but threw his wicket away playing a rash shot off Marco Jansen just after completing his half century. Since then, Rishabh Pant and Ravichandran Ashwin played positive cricket and India would really hope that these two see through the final session as it is the last known pair India could bank on while South Africa would come all guns blazing and will look to fold India's innings as quickly as they can. An interesting final session coming up. Join us at 6.30 pm IST (1 pm GMT) for that.

Session Summary - 25 overs, 93 runs, 2 wickets. That's a session that will once again go in favour of the Proteas and are in the driver's seat now. India were doing well in the opening hour of the game but the complexion of the game changed when Duanne Olivier struck twice of successive deliveries. India entered Lunch on the back foot with 53-3 and post that, they needed a partnership badly. KL Rahul and Hanuma Vihari were motoring along really well and started to build a nice partnership but just when it started to look threatening, Kagiso Rabada got the better of Hanuma Vihari and broke the stand to put South Africa on top.

FOUR! Last ball before Tea and Ashwin sends it towards the boundary! A nicely tossed up delivery on off. Ashiwn plants his front foot forward and creams it through covers for a lovely boundary. He is looking in excellent touch. Keshav Maharaj thought that there was a chance there but it's a boundary for India and they are 146/5 at Tea on Day 1.
An arm ball on off this time. Ashwin defends this off the back foot.
Slower in the air on off again. Ashwin blocks this off the front foot.
Lovely loopy delivery on off again. Ashwin pushes this off the front foot towards the off side.
Another nicely tossed up delivery on off. Ashwin drives it crisply through covers and gets a couple. Bavuma runs behind it and cuts it off.
Time for some spin! Keshav Maharaj is introduced into the attack.
A loopy delivery on off. Ashwin drives it to covers this time.
FOUR BYES! A short ball around leg that takes off from a length. It bounces very high and goes over the batter and keeper's head for a boundary.
NO BALL! A good yorker on middle from 'round the wicket by Jansen. Ashwin plays it comfortably to mid-wicket for a single. Jansen overstepped and will have to reload again.
A short ball on middle. Ashwin pulls it comfortably to deep mid-wicket and gets a couple.
Play and a miss! A short and wide delivery outside off. Ashwin looks to cut it but misses. He is in no mood to miss out on any scoring opportunity.
Jansen bowls this back of a length on off. Ashwin blocks it towards the on side.
Back of a length, outside off. Ashwin punches it off the back foot to covers.
On a length and angling into middle. Ashwin defends it towards the on side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Pant lets it go again.
On a length, on middle. Pant blocks it towards the on side.
A nice good-length delivery around off this time. Pant leaves it alone.
Pant charges down the track to hit a big shot here. Ngidi sees it and bowls this fuller and outside off. No shot played by Pant in the end. Lungi Ngidi gives a good smile back to Pant.
Another length delivery on off. Pant is solid in his defence again.
A length ball, on middle. Pant defends it nicely towards the on side.
Back of a length on middle. Ashwin defends it towards the on side.

FOUR! Another boundary for Ashwin but it's a lucky boundary this time. A full ball from 'round the wicket on off. Ashwin is expecting a short ball and is stuck on his crease as he looks to drive. He gets a thick outside edge and the ball flies through the gap between gully and third slip for a boundary.
A full ball, on middle. Pant drives it straight back past the bowler for a single this time.
Jansen bowls a good short ball on off this time. Pant is hurried on his defensive shot and the ball loops in the air. It goes towards gully but falls short of the fielder.
A short ball this time but down the leg side. Pant has nothing to do with it.
A good-length delivery outside off. Pant leaves it alone this time.
FOUR! Another superb shot by Ashwin! Ngidi bowls this full on off. Ashwin drives it through covers this time for another boundary. Ashwin is looking quite positive here.
A good-length delivery outside off. Ashwin lets it go this time.
A good short ball again on off. Like Rahul, Ashwin goes for the pull shot and gets a top edge. The ball luckily for him falls in the vacant area towards deep square leg and he gets a couple.
On a length, on off this time. Ashwin is deep in his crease and defends it.

FOUR! Nice shot by Ashwin! A full ball, on off. Ashwin drives it with the full face of his blade and gets it past mid on for a beautiful boundary. He is a capable batter and India would hope that he continues to bat and give support to Pant.
A good-length delivery around off. Ashwin gets the inside edge of his blade onto his pads.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Ravichandran Ashwin gets up on his toes and fends it to the leg side for a single.
Ravichandran Ashwin walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! This is a big, big wicket for South Africa! KL Rahul departs after battling so hard for his fifty but he is gone now and India lose half of their side. A good short ball from 'round the wicket from young Jansen. Rahul takes the challenge and looks to pull it. But gets a huge top edge. The ball goes high in the air towards fine leg and Rabada there takes a fine catch. That is the shortest boundary on the ground but Rahul fails to clear it. South Africa have a big opening now. South Africa are into the all-rounders now.
Commentary.Howout: c Kagiso Rabada b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Another delivery in that channel around off. Rahul leaves it alone again. He has been quite good in leaving the balls today.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahul leaves it alone this time. This is good bowling from Jansen.
On a length this time on off. Rahul is as solid as ever and defends it towards the off side.
A fuller delivery but way outside off. Rahul lets it go comfortably.
Good-length ball, on middle. Rishabh Pant defends it back to the bowler.
Length ball, on leg. Rishabh Pant defends it to the leg side.
Length ball, down leg. Rishabh Pant looks to flick but misses.

FIFTY for KL Rahul! That keeps a little low off the length but Rahul is upto the task and he gets the inside half of his blade as he looks to defend. The ball rolls towards square leg and he gets a single. Another fine knock from Rahul as he gets to his fifty.  Rahul is leading from the front here and he has looked class apart from others today.
On a length again, on off. Rahul is solid in his defence.
Ngidi starts with a good-length delivery around off. Rahul leaves it alone. Nice leave by Rahul.
Jansen bowls this on a length, on middle. Pant solidly defends it onto the turf.
Jansen goes more short this time, around off. Pant leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter on off. Pant punches it to covers this time.
A full ball, on off. Pant drives it back to the bowler. This is a good length against Pant.
Jansen pulls his length back this time and bowls this on the off stump. Pant blocks it out.
A full delivery outside off with a hint of away swing. Pant leans forward and drives it through covers for a couple.
Back of a length, on off. Rahul defends it solidly towards the off side.
This time an even better short ball angling into the body. Rahul does well and sways away from the line off the ball.
A short ball this time on off. Rahul ducks under it.
FOUR! good shot by Rahul! A short ball around leg. Rahul gets back and pulls it fine towards long leg for a boundary. Nice placement.
A length delivery outside off. Rahul lets it go.
In the air...but safe! Back of a length, on middle. It hurries on Rahul a little as he looks to defend it. He gets a top edge but falls in the vacant area just away from the turf.
NO BALL! Good-length delivery on off with a little away shape there. Rahul defends it towards the off side. No ball called as Rabada overstepped.
On a length, on off. Pant solidly defends it back to the bowler.
A full ball, outside off. This is a length for Pant to drive but he resists. Leaves it alone.
A good-length delivery on off. Pant gets forward nicely and defends it.
Fuller and on leg, Rishabh Pant flicks it past short leg for a brace.
Sharp bouncer, on middle. KL Rahul swivel-pulls it to fine leg for a single.
A full ball, on middle. Rahul clips it to wide of mid on and gets a couple this time.
Good comeback by Rabada! A good-length delivery around off. Pant pushes forward to defend it but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.

FOUR! Pant likes to play his shot and he gets this one away!  A short ball, outside off. Pant stays deep in his crease and slaps it in front of square for a boundary. This man will get his runs quickly that can be guaranteed.
A harmless delivery wide outside off. Pant leaves it alone again.
Rabada pulls his length back a little this time and bowls this outside off. Pant lets it go.
Lovely drive again. A full ball, on off. Pant drives it through covers this time and gets two runs again.
A full ball, on off. Pant drives it straight back past the bowler and gets a couple. This is a good length from Rabada.
Outside off, back of a length. KL Rahul leaves it untouched.
On a good length, on off. KL Rahul stays solid in his defence.
Short of a length, on off. KL Rahul lets it sail through. Initially thought of playing an upper cut but settles for a leave in the end.
Short ball, on middle. KL Rahul ducks underneath.

FOUR! He is showing everyone how to bat on this wicket. That is beautifully hit. Short of a length, on off. KL Rahul hangs back and punches it through covers. The ball races away to the fence. Moves to 42!
Good-length ball, down leg. KL Rahul looks to tuck but misses. South Africa appeal for a caught behind but the umpire says no.
Outside off, on a length. Left alone by Pant.
On a good length, outside off, nipping away. Rishabh Pant shoulders arms.

Drinks! So just when India were building a good partnership, Kagiso Rabada strikes! Hanuma Vihari departs and India are four down now. South African bowlers have bowled well in this post-lunch session and they will be looking to run through the Indian lower order now. Rishabh Pant walks out to the middle now and this pair is critical for India now.

OUT! CAUGHT! What a catch by Rassie van der Dussen! Just when the partnership was starting to threaten, South Africa find a way to break it and Kagiso Rabada gets his first wicket. Back of a length, on off, coming back in. Hanuma Vihari looks to defend but the ball gets a little big on him. It came off his gloves and pops up towards short leg. Rassie van der Dussen leaps to his left and completes a fabulous one-handed catch. Just plucked it out of thin air to send Hanuma Vihari packing. Temba Bavuma will now be a relieved man as that dropped catch hasn't cost much. India are four down now. South Africa at the top.
Commentary.Howout: c Rassie van der Dussen b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Short of a length, on off. Hanuma Vihari taps it to the off side.
On the pads, KL Rahul clips it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
On a good length, outside off, moving away. KL Rahul shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari shoulders arms.
On a good length, on middle. Hanuma Vihari defends it back to the bowler.

Back of a length, outside off. Pushed towards covers.
Close! Back of a length, on off. Hanuma Vihari looks to punch it off the back foot. The ball goes off the inside edge onto the pads. He is lucky that the ball didn't roll back to disturb the stumps.
Short, on middle and leg. Hanuma Vihari sits under it.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Short of a length again, on leg. KL Rahul pulls it to deep square leg. He has played that nicely but the fielder in the deep cuts it off and keeps it down to a couple.
Short of a length, outside off. KL Rahul shoulders arms.
Length ball, on off. KL Rahul pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Length ball, outside off. KL Rahul gets forward and drives it through covers. No chance for fielders to stop that one and it races away to the fence.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. KL Rahul lets it sail through.
A bouncer, on middle and leg. KL Rahul leaves it alone. No ball called as Kagiso Rabada has overstepped.
Tap and run! On a length, on off. KL Rahul taps it to cover-point for a single.
Back of a length, on leg. Hanuma Vihari clips it to short fine leg for a single.

Another delivery in that channel around off. Vihari is upto the task and leaves it alone.

Back of a length, on off. Vihari solidly defends this off the back foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Rahul plays it past short leg for a single.

Back of a length, on off. Rahul defends this solidly off the back foot.

Back of a length, on off. Vihari blocks it solidly towards the off side.

Good-length delivery on middle. Vihari defends this back to the bowler.

Back of a length, around leg. Vihari looks to flick it but gets hit on his hips this time.
On a length and seaming into Vihari this time. He looks to clip it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Jaffa! A good-length delivery around off. Forcing Vihari to play at it who pushes forward to defend but the ball seams away to beat the outside edge of his blade.

A fuller delivery on middle this time. Vihari drives it to mid-wicket. He gets this off the inside half of his blade.
Jansen bowls this short on middle. Vihari ducks under it comfortably.
Back of a length, on leg. KL Rahul looks to tuck but misses. That goes off his hips to fine leg for a couple of leg byes.
Short of a length, outside off. KL Rahul lets it go.
Uppish but safe! Length ball, on leg. Hanuma Vihari tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Fuller in length, on off. Hanuma Vihari knocks it back to the bowler. Lungi Ngidi collects it on his followthrough and mimes a throw as Hanuma Vihari was out of his crease.
Good-length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari shoulders arms.
FOUR! First runs after Lunch! This will also get Hanuma Vihari moving. Lovely drive that. Fuller and on off, Hanuma Vihari gets forward and drives it towards long off for a boundary.
Third consecutive maiden! Fuller this time, outside off, angling away. KL Rahul lets it be.
Short of a length again, on off. KL Rahul ignores that one.
Back of a length, on off. KL Rahul hops and defends it out.
Well bowled! Bangs a short ball, on middle. The ball hurries onto him and KL Rahul does well in the end to sway away from it.
Length ball, outside off, angling away. KL Rahul leaves it untouched.
Fuller, outside off. KL Rahul with an easy leave.
Ooohs and ahhs from behind the stumps! Good-length ball, in the fourth stump channel. Hanuma Vihari watches the ball closely and then lets it go. Back-to-back maidens!
Length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari defends it to the off side.
Fuller, outside off. Hanuma Vihari lunges and blocks it out.
On a good length, on off, shaping away. Hanuma Vihari stays solid in his defence.
Length ball, an outswinger, outside off. Hanuma Vihari taps it to point.
Fuller, outside off. Hanuma Vihari drives it crisply but straight to covers.
On middle, defended off the front foot by Rahul. A maiden to begin with after Lunch.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
Top nut! Similar delivery how Mayank Agarwal got out. Good-length ball, on off, moving away. KL Rahul looks to defend keeping his bat close to the body. The ball zips past the outside edge.
On a good length, on off, coming back in. KL Rahul is solid in his defence.
Back of a length, on middle. KL Rahul hops and blocks it out one-handedly.
Starts with a good-length ball, on middle. KL Rahul blocks it on the leg side.

We are back for the middle session! South African players stride out to the middle. KL Rahul and Hanuma Vihari jog out to resume their innings as well. Marco Jansen to start with the ball for South Africa.
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 …

South African bowlers bowled well especially in the second hour of the play as they found appreciable movement from the pitch. Kagiso Rabada and Duanne Olivier were off-target initially but soon Ngidi and Jansen created pressure with their good lines and lengths and eventually, Jansen got the important wicket of Mayank Agarwal. Soon Duanne Olivier got into his rhythm in his comeback match and shifted the momentum in South Africa’s favour with two big wickets of Pujara and Rahane. South Africa have bagged this opening session of the second Test match. Will India fight back? Or will South African bowlers continue to dominate? Join us at 4:10 pm IST (10:40 am GMT) to find out.

This has been quite an engrossing first session of the Test match. Indian did well to blunt the new ball and it was KL Rahul again who was solid in his defence this morning. Mayank Agrawal also looked good while he was there but eventually departed after a good start again. Pujara came in and played out some nervy moments but lost his wicket just at the stroke of the Lunch. Rahane followed soon as he departed for a golden duck. In the end, the session which was looking like going India’s way was pulled by South Africa on their side with those twin strikes.
Very full, on the pads. Hanuma Vihari tickles it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 1!
Short of a length, outside off. Left alone.

NOT OUT! Fuller in length, on middle. Vihari looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Loud appeal from South Africa for an lbw but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar decides to challenge the umpire. UltraEdge shows that there was an inside edge. The on-field decision stands and South Africa burn another review.

Review! South Africa have taken a review for LBW here. This has hit Vihari low in the pads. The replay rolls in and the UltraEdge shows that there is bat involved as he got the inside edge onto his pads. So the decision stays and South Africa lose their review.
On a good length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari shoulders arms.
Good-length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari with an easy leave.
Back of a length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari fends it away to the off side.
Good length, on middle. KL Rahul blocks it out.
On a length, on leg. KL Rahul defends it out.
Length ball, angling in on leg. Hanuma Vihari clips it to square leg for one.
On a good length, outside off. Hanuma Vihari shoulders arms.
Length ball, outside off. Hanuma Vihari defends it out.
Down the leg side. Hanuma Vihari looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length, on middle. Hanuma Vihari clips it behind square on the leg side to get off the mark with a single. 50 up for India.
Hanuma Vihari does well to negotiate the hat-trick ball. Good-length ball, on off, shaping away. Hanuma Vihari taps it to the off side off the gloves.
Hanuma Vihari is the next batter in.

OUT! TAKEN! Two in two for Duanne Olivier and gets a big one. Ajinkya Rahane departs for a golden duck. South African players are all over Duanne Olivier. It is also his 50th Test wicket. Good-length ball, outside off, shaping further away. Ajinkya Rahane pushes at it tentatively away from his body. The ball goes off the outside edge and flies to the third slip fielder. Keegan Petersen does well to move to his right and complete the catch. Really poor shot from Ajinkya Rahane and has to depart. Duanne Olivier is on a hat-trick now.
Commentary.Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Duanne Olivier

Commentary.Commentary: Ajinkya Rahane is the next batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT! If India were to finish this session with no further hiccups they would've done remarkably well. But that isn't the case. Duanne Olivier had other plans and lets out a huge roar. He strikes and bags a wicket. Plans were clear from South Africa to continue bowling shorter and finally, they reap rewards. Duanne Olivier bowls a short-of-a-length delivery, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara dangles his bat without any conviction. The ball gets a little too big on him and lobs off the shoulder of the bat towards point. Temba Bavuma takes the simplest of catches there and Cheteshwar Pujara has to walk back to the pavilion with yet another low score.
Commentary.Howout: c Temba Bavuma b Duanne Olivier

Commentary.Commentary: Good-length ball, on off, shaping in. Cheteshwar Pujara is cut in half as he gets struck on the thigh pad.
Short ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara squats and sways away from the line.
Outside off, on a good length. KL Rahul shoulders arms.
On a good length, on middle and leg, coming back in. KL Rahul looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Short ball from Rabada, on middle. KL Rahul sits under it and evades the line comfortably.
Length ball, on off. KL Rahul comes forward and pushes it to mid-wicket.
On a good length, on off. KL Rahul taps it to the off side.
FOUR! Easy pickings! Back of a length, on leg. KL Rahul glances it to fine leg for a boundary.
Length ball, in the channel outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara defends it to the leg side.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Cheteshwar Pujara gets inside the line and deflects it off the thigh pads to the keeper.
Short ball, on the bodyline. KL Rahul swivel-pulls it over the backward square leg fielder. Will only get a single.
On a good length, right on top of off. KL Rahul covers the line and blocks it down onto the deck.
FOUR! Straight down the ground! That will race away. Fuller in length, on middle. KL Rahul shows full face of the bat and pushes it with ease towards long on for a boundary.
Fuller, on off, with a hint of inward movement. KL Rahul drives it back to the bowler.
On a length, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara meets it with a dead bat.
On a good length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara guides it towards the third slip fielder.
Back of a length, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara hops and tucks it on the leg side.
Some swing there! Little fuller, outside off, shaping away. Cheteshwar Pujara prods and blocks it out to the off side.
Good-length outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Spraying down leg this one. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
A fuller ball to end the over on middle. Rahul drives it straight to mid on.
On a length and nipping into the batter this time. Rahul looks to flick it but misses. He gets rapped up high on the pads but no damage done.

Ohh..the plan nearly worked! A good short ball angling into the body this time. Pujara looks to defend it as the ball bounces sharply. He gets the inside half of his blade and ball loops in the air. It falls just away from the diving leg gully and Pujara gets a single.
A full ball, on off. Pujara defends it towards the off side.
Duanne Olivier bowls this fuller on middle this time. Pujara is aware of the ploy of bowling short and then bowling it full. He defends this off the front foot.
Back of a length, on middle. Pujara blocks this off the back foot solidly this time.
A proper short delivery on middle this time. Rahul ducks under it.
Another delivery that is shorter on length around off. Rahul is equal to the task and defends it onto the turf.
Jansen goes shorter this time on off. Rahul rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Ohh..Another ball that comes back into the batter and bounces sharply. Pujara defends it aerially off the inside half of his blade to fine leg for a single this time.
Good-length delivery on middle and nipping in. Pujara gets the inside half of his blade as he looks to defend. The ball goes towards mid-wicket.
Back of a length, outside off. Pujara has nothing to do with it and lets it go.
Slightly shorter again, around off. Rahul gets deep in his crease and pushes it with soft hands to square on the off side.
Duanne Olivier goes back of a length again on off. Rahul rides the bounce and punches it towards the off side.
Shorter length delivery on off. Rahul sways away from the line of the ball this time. Good bowling this.
That's a beauty! A good-length delivery around off this time. The ball nips into the batter with good bounce. Rahul stays inside the line of the ball and lets it go.
Back of a length, on middle again. Rahul is right behind it to block it towards the on side.
Duanne Olivier starts with a slightly shorter length delivery on middle. Rahul rides the bounce and defends it towards the on side.
Jansen goes short this time around leg. Pujara is quick to judge the length of the ball and ducks under it.
A good-length delivery outside off and Pujara decides to leave it alone again. Good carry for Jansen.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Pujara leaves it alone again.
Jansen pulls his length back a little time and gets a good seam movement into the batter. This is around off and Pujara leaves it alone.
Jansen goes fuller this time on off. Pujara drives it to covers.
A good-length delivery on off. Cheteshwar Pujara defends this off the front foot solidly.

Ohhh..That's so close! Lungi Ngidi pulls his length back a little this time on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to defend but there is some extra bounce and the ball hits the inside half of his blade and goes past short leg. A single taken.
Hitting that good-length again on the off stump line. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks this off the front foot.
A good-length delivery again. This time a touch wider and Cheteshwar Pujara lets it go.
A fuller delivery on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara pushes this off the front foot to mid on. This is good bowling from Lungi Ngidi.
Drifting on the pads this time. Rahul flicks it to fine leg and gets a single. Excitement again from South African players but there was nothing there.
A good-length delivery in that channel around off. Seams away sharply and beats the outside edge of Rahul's blade as he pushes forward to defend.
Beautifully bowled! Fuller, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara gets forward and defends it out. A wicket-maiden from Marco Jansen. Top over from the youngster.
Back of a length, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara stands tall and blocks it right under his eyes.
Outside off, on a good length, moving away. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Bangs a short ball this time, on middle and leg. Cheteshwar Pujara ducks under it.
On a good length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara leaves it alone.
Cheteshwar Pujara walks in at number 3.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Marco Jansen is right on money after the break. Exactly what South Africa needed. That's top bowling from the youngster. Hurls in a good-length ball from over the wicket, on off, angling away. Mayank Agarwal is tempted to have a push at it. The ball nips away and kisses the outside edge. Kyle Verreynne makes no mistake behind the stumps and South Africa have got the breakthrough. Marco Jansen is all pumped up and Mayank Agarwal will have to take the long walk back.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Marco Jansen

Commentary.Commentary: Drinks! Good solid start for India as both Indian openers have successfully played out the first hour of this Test match much like they did at Centurion. South African bowlers took some time to find their lines and length but the introduction of Lungi Ngidi into the attack has shown that there is enough keep in the surface for the seam bowlers. Can South African bowlers break this partnership after the drinks?
On a length, on off. KL Rahul taps it to point. Very good over from Lungi Ngidi. Hitting the perfect line and lengths. Just a single from it and now it's time for the players to get some refreshment.
Little movement this time! Good-length ball, on off. KL Rahul dabs it towards the slip cordon.
Terrific stuff! On a good length, outside off. KL Rahul continues his leaving spree outside off.
Goes full, onto the pads. Maybe trying to hit the pads for an lbw. Mayank Agarwal clips it to deep square leg for a single.
And again! On a good length, outside off, shaping away. Mayank Agarwal yet again shoulders arms. Lungi Ngidi is being very disclipined with his line and lengths here.
Nice bowling! Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Mayank Agarwal shoulders arms.
On a length, outside off, moving away. KL Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Good bounce! On a good length, on off, coming back in. KL Rahul tries to defend but gets hit on the gloves as there was some extra bounce on that one.
Errs in his line this time. Back of a length, down leg. KL Rahul leaves it alone.
Fullish, outside off, angling away. KL Rahul offers no shot.
Back of a length, on middle, Mayank Agarwal hops and tucks it on the leg side for a single.
Fuller and outside off, angling away. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Marco Jansen is into the attack now.

Once again! On a good length, in the fourth stump channel. KL Rahul looks to defend but the ball misses his outside edge. Really top bowling this. Lungi Ngidi is getting the ball to move and is asking right questions to KL Rahul.

Lovely movement off the seam! Lungi Ngidi was the star bowler in the first Test and is troubling here as well. Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. KL Rahul gets squared up in his defence. The ball beats the outside edge by a whisker.
Outside off, on a length, moving away. KL Rahul leaves it for the keeper to collect.
Wide enough of outside off. KL Rahul is not troubled by that line and leaves it untouched.
Back of a length this time, in the fourth stump channel. KL Rahul lets it sail through.
Nicely bowled! On a good length, outside off, nipping away. KL Rahul looks to defend but the ball moves a little more and misses the outside edge.
A full ball from Rabada this time on off. Mayank Agarwal pushes it aerially to the right of Rabada and gets it through mid on for a couple. Rabada made an effort there to get a hand on it but failed.
Back of a length, around off. Mayank Agarwal gets back and blocks it with soft hands square on the off side.

Shouts of catch but the ball falls just short! Good-length ball, coming back in, on middle. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball lobs up towards short leg but there was no short leg in place. The man from square leg comes forward and dives ahead to take the catch but it falls just short of him. Kagiso Rabada sits down and has his hand over his head.
Once again! Sprays this one down the leg side, swinging further away. Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone. Kyle Verreynne does well to collect the ball moving to his left.
Sliding down the leg side this time, Mayank Agarwal looks to flick but misses.
Angling in, on middle, on a good length. Mayank Agarwal pushes it to mid on.
Another delivery in that channel outside off. The ball seams away with good bounce again as Rahul lets it go.
A good-length delivery outside off. The ball seams away sharply. Rahul leaves it alone.
Slightly shorter on off. Rahul defends it solidly towards the off side.
A good-length delivery around off. Good away movement there. Rahul leaves it alone.
He finds an edge this time but safe! A good-length delivery around off. Rahul pushes at it with soft hands and gets a thick edge which falls short of the third slip fielder.
First change of the day. Lungi Ngidi is brought into the attack. He replaces Duanne Olivier.
On the money first ball! A good-length ball, on middle. Hint of away swing there. KL Rahul defends this off the back foot.
Back of a length on off. Mayank Agarwal lets it go this time. Good bounce and seam movement for Rabada there.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it solidly off the back foot.
Good-length ball, coming in, on middle. Mayank Agarwal looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge to point.
Back of a length, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal defends it on the leg side.
Outside off, on a good length. Left alone by Mayank Agarwal.
FOUR! A full ball, on the pads and Mayank Agarwal puts it away. He gets the timing right and nails it through backward square leg for a boundary.

FOUR! This time a lucky boundary for Rahul. Good-length ball, around off. Rahul tries to push it off the back foot but gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes through the gap between third slip and gully and goes for a boundary.

FOUR! Fuller and punished by Rahul this time. A full ball on middle. Rahul gets forward and just pushes it past mid on for a boundary. Rahul is batting cautiously but at the same time he is not missing out on an opportunity to score runs.
Back of a length, outside off. KL Rahul leaves it alone comfortably.

South Africa have taken a review for a caught behind. UltraEdge shows no bat involved. That came off his shoulders and that's why the excitement. The on-field decision stands and South Africa lose their first review.

NOT OUT! Ohhh...A good short ball on off from Duanne Olivier. KL Rahul is surprised by the bounce and tries to defend it but gets in an awkward position. The ball hits his shoulders and goes back to the keeper. There is an huge appeal from South African players but the umpire is unmoved. They review it but the replays show it is hitting shoulders and KL Rahul survives. Another good decision by the umpire.
Slightly fuller this time from Duanne Olivier on off. KL Rahul defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Good-length delivery around off. KL Rahul solidly defends it towards the off side.
FOUR! Nice timing from Mayank Agarwal! An overpitched delivery on middle. Mayank Agarwal presents the full face of his blade and creams it past mid on for a boundary. Good shot!
On a good length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal shoulders arms.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it with soft hands towards the slip cordon.
Back of a length, on off. Mayank Agarwal hops and blocks it out solidly.
A good-length delivery on middle and nipping in this time. Mayank Agarwal gets the inside edge onto his pads as he looks to defend it.
Nice delivery from Rabada. A full ball with a hint of away swing on off. Mayank Agarwal defends it to mid off.
A full ball this time from Duanne Olivier on off. KL Rahul gets well forward and defends it towards the off side.
A good-length delivery around off. KL Rahul stays deep in his crease and pushes it with soft hands to gully.

Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. KL Rahul looks to push but gets beaten on the outside edge. South African players are very excited as they think that came off the outside edge and they appeal for a caught behind. But the umpire says no. There was definitely some noise there but South Africa opt against the review. Well, replay shows that the noise was of KL Rahul's bat brushing the pads. Good decision from the umpire and good call from South Africa as well to not to take the review.
Duanne Olivier pulls his length back a little this time on middle. KL Rahul defends it off the back foot.
This time he drifts on the pads. Mayank Agarwal flicks it to fine leg and gets a single this time.
Ohh...Good outswing there for Duanne Olivier. He bowls this fuller outside off and gets a good away movement.  Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone.
Outside off, on a length. KL Rahul lets it be.
Length ball, on middle. KL Rahul defends it to short leg.
Top nut! Good-length ball, in the fourth stump channel, nipping away. KL Rahul stands up on his toes and looks to defend. The ball whistles past the outside edge and carries through to the keeper.
Bangs a short ball but way down leg. Easy for KL Rahul to duck under it and sway away from the line.
Length ball, on off, coming back in. Mayank Agarwal looks to push. The ball goes off the inside edge to square leg for a single.
On a good length, on middle. Mayank Agarwal blocks it from the crease.
Back of a length, outside off, shaping away. KL Rahul goes back and shoulders arms. That's mich better from Duanne Olivier except for the no ball he bowled.
Very full, outside off. KL Rahul pushes it towards point.
Back of a length, outside off. KL Rahul defends it towards extra cover.
NO BALL! A waist height full toss, on middle. KL Rahul defends it on the ground. No ball called a given a first warning too.
On a good length, coming back in, on off. KL Rahul presses forward and looks to defend. But the ball goes past the outside edge.
Duanne Olivier goes fuller this time around off. KL Rahul presses forward to defend this inside the line of the ball and lets it go. The ball seams back into the batter a little this time.

This is much better from Duanne Olivier! Good-length ball, around off, shaping away. KL Rahul leaves it alone. He has worked on that off stump technique really well since the last couple of years. Leaving alone deliveries that are close to off stump.
On a good length, outside off, nipping away. Mayank Agarwal is happy to leave this one. He shoulders arms.
FOUR! Shot! Third boundary for him. Little fuller, outside off, shaping away. Mayank Agarwal opens the face of the bat and drives it through covers for a boundary.
On a good length, around off, shaping away. Mayank Agarwal watches it closely and makes a leave.
KL Rahul is off the mark as well. On a length, on leg. KL Rahul comes forward and tucks it behind square on the leg side for a single.
Fuller this time, outside off. KL Rahul leans and drives it. But straight towards covers.
On a good length, on middle. KL Rahul stands up and meets it with a straight bat.

FOUR! A poor ball from Duanne Olivier. A full toss, on middle. Mayank Agarwal doesn't miss out on those. He pushes it past the mid off fielder for a boundary. Starts the over with a bouncer and keeps everyone excited but ends with a full toss. 8 runs from the over.
On a length, outside off. Mayank Agarwal lets it sail through.

FOUR! First runs for India and Mayank Agarwal. He gets off the mark with a boundary. Length ball, outside off. Mayank Agarwal leans onto it and creams it through covers. The ball races away to the boundary.
Good-length ball, coming into the right-hander, on middle and leg. Mayank Agarwal defends it onto the deck.
Length delivery, outside off, Mayank Agarwal leaves it alone. Not a lot of swing there!
Duanne Olivier starts with a bouncer, on middle. Mayank Agarwal sits under this one. Good carry for Kyle Verreynne.
Duanne Olivier to start from the other end.
Length ball, on middle and leg. KL Rahul comes half forward and taps the ball on the leg side. A good start from Kagiso Rabada. Tidy stuff from him. A maiden!
And again! Similar line and length, around the fifth stump channel. KL Rahul looks to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Beauty! That's the line Kagiso Rabada will be targeting. Good-length ball, around off, nipping away. KL Rahul pokes at it tentatively. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Back of a length, swinging away now, down leg. KL Rahul at first looks to tuck but then shoulders arms. Kyle Verreynne moves to his left to collect the ball.
Back of a length now, on middle. KL Rahul stands up on his toes and blocks it with a dead bat.
Kagiso Rabada starts with a good-length delivery, outside off, shaping away. KL Rahul watchfully leaves it untouched.

We are done with the anthems and now South African players make their way out to the centre. So do the Indian openers, KL Rahul and Mayank Agarwal! South Africans take a knee in their support for the BLM movement. Indian players keep their hand on their heart and we are all ready to begin now. Kagiso Rabada to start for South Africa. Here we go...
Both the sides stride out to the middle for their respective national anthems. It will be India's national anthem first and is followed by the national anthem of South Africa.

PITCH REPORT - Morne Morkel says that the pitch will be a touch slow to start off but will quicken up as the day progresses. Mentions that there are a few cracks which could open up as well. Tells that it is a good wicket. Says that as a bowler, one needs to bowl tight lines.

Ajinkya Rahane is down for a chat, he says that he loves this ground and it gives good vibes. Mentions that the beauty of a Test match is that you start from zero. Tells that they celebrated a bit on winning the first Test but they know they have two more Tests to go and are focusing on winning those. Tells that it is all about starting fresh and get use to the conditions and play accordingly. Says that he is feeling good mentally and it is all about converting starts into bigger scores. Tells that he batted well in the last Test but was disappointed with the way he got out in both the innings.

Dean Elgar, the skipper of South Africa, says that Quinton de Kock has been an important player for them and he has been a great performer for them over the years. Says that they need to move on now. Mentions that they need to put up on a great performance and there are a lot of positives and they can't wait to get the second Test to get underway. Informs that there are two changes. Kyle Verreynne is in for Quinton de Kock and Duanne Olivier is in for Wiaan Mulder.

KL Rahul, the Indian skipper, says that Virat has an upper back spasm and hopefully he will be fit for the next Test. He adds that it is a dream to captain the country and he feels privileged to do the job. He adds that Wanderers has been a good ground for them and hopefully they will play well today. He adds that Hanuma Vihari will replace Virat Kohli. He mentions that they played good cricket in the first Test and would want to continue the good work and work on the mistakes they made in the first Test match.

South Africa (Playing XI) - Dean Elgar (C), Aiden Markram, Keegan Petersen, Rassie van der Dussen, Temba Bavuma, Kyle Verreynne (WK) (In place of Quinton de Kock), Marco Jansen, Keshav Maharaj, Kagiso Rabada, Duanne Olivier (In place of Wiaan Mulder), Lungi Ngidi.

India (Playing XI) - KL Rahul (C), Mayank Agarwal, Cheteshwar Pujara, Ajinkya Rahane, Hanuma Vihari (In place of Virat Kohli), Rishabh Pant (WK), Ravichandran Ashwin, Shardul Thakur, Mohammed Shami, Jasprit Bumrah, Mohammed Siraj.
TOSS - Both the captains are out in the middle. Up goes the coin and lands in the favour of India. They have elected to BAT first.

Update - Well, well, well, the BIG NEWS from the middle is that Virat Kohli is going to miss the second Test. KL Rahul will lead the side. There is no clarity though that why Virat Kohli is not playing. Toss coming up shortly.

MORE WORRIES FOR ENGLAND. As if, the current Ashes series status was not big enough. The fourth Test is scheduled to be played in Sydney, but England landed without their head coach, their bowling coach, their spin bowling coach and their strength and conditioning coach. To make up for their absence, they had sent an SOS call to former ODI captain Adam Hollioake only for him to be ruled out on the eve of his arrival. He had become a close contact to someone who had tested positive. And the latest news coming in is that there is some kind of Covid scare amongst the net bowlers as well which has interrupted England's practice sessions big time. Tough days.

CRICKET UPDATES - Well, there is a Test match going on Down Under in New Zealand. Thanks to their time zones, it is pretty difficult to catch those games in action. This New Year's Test has certainly been a surprise. We all know that traditionally, pitches in New Zealand get better and better to bat on as the days progress. But not many would have imagined this kind of a fight from Bangladesh. First, they restricted the home side to 328 and then batted beautifully, to record a score of 401/6 while going into Stumps at Day 3. For a team which has demolished the likes of India, England, South Africa, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, West Indies and Bangladesh at home in the last 5 years, it has been a real toil for all the bowlers.

RETIREMENT UPDATES - Well, It has been a week of retirements. First, Harbhajan Singh fomally announced his retirement a few days ago. Then, Quinton de Kock shocked everyone by announcing his retirement from Tests, piling more agony on South Africa. And now, the latest news coming in is that Pakistan's MOHAMMAD HAFEEZ HAS PUT DOWN HIS PAPERS TOO, from international cricket. The 41-year old veteran confirms his availability for franchise cricket.

South Africa, on the other hand, will be hurting after that loss in Centurion. They have a proud home record and will be looking to make a strong statement by winning this Test match. They were handed a double-blow on the final day of the first Test match as the loss was coupled with the shocking news of Quinton de Kock retiring from Test cricket. Their bowling is in comparatively safer hands with Kagiso Rabada and Lungi Ngidi leading the way but the batters need to step up against this potent Indian pace battery. This is a do-or-die game for South Africa and they can take some inspiration from their series win in 2006 when they came back to clinch the series 2-1 after suffering a defeat in the first Test match. Can they repeat the same performance against this strong Indian unit? Or will India create history by clinching their first-ever Test series in South Africa? We shall find out over the course of the next 5 days. Stay tuned for toss and further updates.

If there is one team in world cricket that has played consistently good cricket in overseas conditions over the last few years, it is India. Under the leadership of Virat Kohli, this Indian team has proved its mettle in the toughest of conditions and are now on the brink of creating history by winning a Test series in South Africa. They dominated the first Test match at Centurion as their lethal fast bowling attack made full use of the conditions. KL Rahul and Mayank Agarwal are in good form  but the concern for India will be the form of the experienced trio of Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli and Ajinkya Rahane but with an opportunity to seal the series in the country where India has never won before, they will be itching to contribute big in this Test match. One more thing, that goes in India’s favour is that Wanderers has been a happy hunting ground for the Indians and they have never lost a Test match at this ground so far.

The action now moves to Wanderers from Centurion where the rampant Indian team will look to create history by winning their first Test series in the rainbow nation. South Africa, on the other hand, have a proud home record and we can expect them to come out all guns blazing in a bid to level the series. On that note, welcome to our coverage of the second Test of this three-match Test series between South Africa and India.

We are back for India's reply! The players stride out to the middle. KL Rahul and Mayank Agarwal are the openers for India. Kagiso Rabada to start the proceedings with the ball. Here we go...

Indian bowling performance was all about Shardul Thakur who got his first five-wicket haul and whenever India was struggling to get the breakthrough he was the one who provided it. All other bowlers were disciplined and the pressure was always kept on from both ends. Shardul Thakur finished with seven wickets and he is the one who has kept India in the game here. It is upto their batters now to gain an upper hand in this Test match they trail by 27 runs which doesn't look threatening. Who will inch ahead at the end of the day? We shall find out. Stay tuned for India's second innings.

South African batters showed resilience out there in the middle on a tricky pitch. Keegan Petersen and Bavuma were especially impressive as they notched up their respective fifties. But despite getting some handy partnerships, the problem of losing wickets in cluster cost South Africa big time. They had a longer tail in this Test match but Jansen and Maharaj had a good partnership in the end and they were eventually bundled out for 229 with crucial lead under their belt.

Shardul Thakur leads the side with a standing ovation. He has been the stand-out bowler for India and ends with figures 7/61- The best ever by an India bowler on South African soil. South Africa lead by 27 runs.

The ball goes off the outside edge and carries through to the keeper. Rishabh Pant dives to his right to collect the ball. Shardul Thakur has been magnificent and has reaped rewards. Session Summary - 25.2 overs, 89 runs, 3 wickets. South Africa were doing really well and it looked like they would enter Lunch unscathed but the dimension of the game changed when Dean Elgar got out and then Shardul Thakur struck twice at the stroke of Lunch to put India in the ascendancy. Two new batters were at the crease post Lunch for the hosts in Temba Bavuma and Kyle Verreynne and they batted beautifully. The duo dealt with some real peaches and scored at a decent clip but Shardul Thakur or as he is called, Lord Shardul Thakur once again got the breakthrough removing Kyle Verreynne. While Bavuma continued on his merry way and brought up his half century but departed immediately. The tail was exposed then and India need just 3 wickets before they come out to bat again. While South Africa would look to add some vital runs and have a decent lead over India. Join us for the final session at 6.30 pm IST (1 pm GMT).
Shardul Thakur leads the side as he has picked up his maiden five-wicket haul in Tests. Just like the first session, India have again comeback with a strong reply in the last hour of this session.

Temba Bavuma walks down the track for some strange reason and Thakur pulls his length back around leg. Bavuma looks to clip it and gets a faint part of his blade. Pant behind the stumps dives to his left and takes a superb catch. Bavuma who was looking so good has to walk back and India are right on top now. There was some confusion regrading the catch taken by Pant but in the end replays show that he has taken it cleanly and Thakur is on a roll here.

... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

Indian bowlers were top-notch this morning but some quality batting by South Africa denied them a breakthrough for the most part of the session. It was the man with the golden arm, Shardul Thakur who eventually got the wicket of South African skipper, Dean Elgar. After his wicket, the pair of Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen were tasted with some quality seam bowling and Shardul Thakur again got into the act with the wickets of Keegan Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen. India have got three wickets in the final half-hour of the first session and will be now looking to dictate terms. Can India continue their fightback with more wickets in the next session? We shall find out as we will be back for the post-lunch session at 4.10 pm IST (10.40 am GMT).

Another session, that looked like going South Africa’s way was pulled back by India with three wickets in the last half hour of the session. In testing conditions where the ball was seaming and swinging quite a bit, South Africa  batted solidly at the start. Both Elgar and Keegan Petersen were solid this morning and despite some quality bowling by Indian bowlers, the pair ensured that India were denied the breakthrough for the major part of the session. Elgar departed just half an hour before Lunch but young Keegan Petersen carried on and got to his maiden Test fifty. But the wickets of Keegan Petersen and Rassie van der Dussen just at the stroke of the Lunch has ensured that India have an opening now.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Things are falling apart for South Africa now. Shardul Thakur has struck not once, not twice, but thrice for India and has put his side back in the game. Back of a length, outside off, coming into the batter. Rassie van der Dussen is caught on the crease as he tries to defend. The ball goes off the inside edge, hits him on the pads and carries through to Rishabh Pant who dives ahead to grab the ball. Shardul Thakur appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Well, well, well, the replay shows that the ball hit the grass before Rishabh Pant caught it but Rassie van der Dussen started walking to the pavilion. So the decision stands. South Africa have been reduced to 102/4 in no time. Shardul Thakur has picked up three wickets in a span of 4.5 overs. Top stuff from the man with the golden arm. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Commentary.Howout: c Rishabh Pant b Shardul Thakur

Shardul Thakur has broken this partnership and India have got the opening now.

PITCH REPORT - Mike Haysman says that the track is very inconsistent and might be worrisome for the batters. Mentions that there are good areas for bowlers to exploit and says that there is a mix of dead and live grass. Tells that the bounce will be variable and there will be movement off the surface. Informs that it rained overnight and the pitch might quicken up. Ends by saying that it is a tough batting wicket.

Ravichandran Ashwin is down for a chat, he says that when he was batting, he took the scoring opportunites and was aware all the time. Tells that Centurion pitch quickened up later but the bounce at Johannesburg is steep and the pitch might get faster as the day progreses. Tells that it is similar to being a fast bowler in India, you have to get used to the conditions and bowl acording to the plans. On Siraj, he says that he will definitely be okay and hopes that he comes out strong and gives his best. Says that they have a wonderful bowling attack and they will look to give their 100 percent and is sure that they can do the job for the team.

Mohammed Siraj bowled an excellent spell on Day 1 before he pulled his hamstring and left the field. It would be interesting to see if he is fit enough to bowl as India need him desperately as the pitch is favouring the pacers and he can be very lethal alongside Jasprit Bumrah, Mohammed Shami and Shardul Thakur.

After bundling out India for just 202, South Africa finished Day 1 with 35-1 where they lost the solitary wicket of Aiden Markram. They still trail by 167 runs and they would hope to cut off the deficit and take a lead over India. On the other hand, India need wickets and need them at a quick pace. The pitch is also expected to get faster and the Indian bowlers will be raring to go. All this is only possible if the weather is favourable for play.

Hello and welcome to Day 2 of the Test match. First things first, it is bright and sunny as of now but there is rain predicted for the second and third session. Still, a lot of time for a result though in this game. So let’s now see what the two teams will be looking to do today.
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 …

Right then, this has been an engrossing day of Test cricket and South Africa seem to be slightly ahead at the end of the day. But India have enough arsenal in their kitty to comeback strongly on Day 2. They just need to remind themselves what happened the last time they played South Africa here in a Test match. In 2018, India were bowled out for 187 in the first innings but responded strongly by dismissing the Proteas for 194. That too, from a strong position of 80/2. Monday may not have been India's best but Tuesday will be a new day. The first ball will be bowled at 1.30 pm IST (8.00 am GMT) but as you know, the buildup will begin well in advance. So do join us early to catch all the action. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Earlier in the day, it was South Africa who dominated the proceedings as they bundled out India for 202 in the first innings. KL Rahul and Ravichandran Ashwin were the only batters who played a worthy knock as others failed to get going. The pitch assisted the South African bowlers and they kept picking wickets at regular intervals. Marco Jansen ended with 4 wickets while Kagiso Rabada and Duanne Olivier ended with 3 each to their name. It is upto the South African batters now to back up their bowlers and put Indians under pressure on Day 2. India, on the other hand, need to keep believing and some early wickets on Day 2 will bring them right back into the game. A crucial second day of this Test match is awaiting us. Can Indian bowlers fight back? Or will South African batters take their team further ahead in this game? Only time will tell.

Indian bowlers bowled with good steam out there after they were bundled out for 202. Shami provided the early breakthrough as he dismissed Aiden Markram for the third time in this series. All other bowlers bowled well but they failed to get another breakthrough. They will be looking to get some early wickets on Day 2 and would be hoping that Siraj who walked off the field at the stroke of Stumps due to a hamstring issue is fit and raring to go tomorrow as he bowled probing line and lengths and troubled Dean Elgar a lot.

The pair of Dean Elgar and Keegan Petersen have done well here to take their team to the end of the play with just one wicket down. The pitch has enough help for the bowlers but this pair has been quite solid. Aiden Markram departed early yet again and South African batters have a tough task ahead of them but this has been a good day for South Africa and they will be looking to build on it on Day 2.

WIDE! Bangs a bouncer now, on middle. Dean Elgar sits under it. Wide called for height.
On a length, on off. Dean Elgar defends it out.
Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Dean Elgar lets it through.

The final innings is set to begin. The Indian players are in a huddle near the ropes, before they spread out to their respective fielding positions. Followed by Aiden Markram and Dean Elgar who walk out to open for South Africa. Jasprit Bumrah to start with the ball.
... FOURTH INNINGS ...

The talk of experienced duo of Pujara and Rahane not scoring runs were put to rest this morning as both of them unleashed a brilliant counter-attacking fifties. This partnership was after India lost both their openers on Day 2 and were under the pump. Things started falling apart for India once Pujara and Rahane fell. But useful contribution by the lower order along with Vihari has ensured that India get that lead to 239 runs. Can the Indian bowlers lead India to their first-ever Test series victory in the rainbow nation? We shall find out.

South African bowlers started on a right note on Day 2 by dismissing both Indian openers early. But leaked far too many runs after that as Rahane and Pujara piled on the runs at a brisk rate. They needed some inspiration this morning and Rabada provided it with three crucial wickets of Rahane, Pujara and Pant. After that, all the bowlers found their mojo and wickets started falling at regular intervals but India still managed to get some crucial runs in the end much to the frustration of the South African bowlers. Chasing over 200 on the Wanderers is tricky and South Africa have a tough task ahead of them.

What a cracker of a game this is turning out to be. Both teams are finding ways to get back into the game just when things looked like drifting away from them. India have been bowled out for 266. South African now need 240 to win this game and level the series.

OUT! TIMBER! Lungi Ngidi does not waste anymore time and sends back Mohammed Siraj on a duck. Lungi Ngidi gets his third wicket of the game. A length ball, on the off stump. Mohammed Siraj stays inside the crease and looks to defend it out but misses. The ball goes through to rattle the off stump. Siraj cannot believe it. India get bowled out for 266 runs.

Drinks! South Africa are just one wicket away from bundling out India here. But India will be happy with the lead they have got now.  Vihari is standing solid there and Thakur provided some great impetus to the innings. How much more can India get with Mohammed Siraj joining Vihari in the middle.

The lead is already over 200. How much more will India be able to add?
