Back of a length again by Rabada. Vihari defends this off the back foot solidly.
Back of  a length, on off. Defended off the back foot.
NO BALL! A short ball on middle this time. Vihari ducks under it. Overstepping by Rabada.

Review! Kyle Verreynne convinces the skipper to take it upstairs for a caught behind review. The UltraEdge shows no spike as the ball passes the blade. The on-field decision of not out does not get overturned. South Africa have only one review in the bank now.

NOT OUT! Back of a length and down the leg side. Vihari looks to clip it but misses. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left and takes a good catch. Kyle Verreynne thinks there is bat invloved and convinces Elgar to go for the review. He takes it but the UltraEdge shows that there is no bat invloved. So Vihari survives.
A good-length delivery outside off. Vihari leaves it alone.
Extra bounce straightaway! A good-length delivery on off and this bounces off the length to hit Vihari on his gloves. He looks to defend and the ball loops towards the off side.
The second session is set to begin. The South African players take the field. Followed by Hanuma Vihari and Shardul Thakur who walk out to bat for India. Kagiso Rabada to start with the ball.
... Day 3, Session 2 ...

Kagiso Rabada was an inspiration with the ball to get his side back in the hunt. The bowlers were taken to the cleaners in the first hour of the session, as Pujara and Rahane were up to the task. But once Rahane fell, the hosts had a sniff and made sure to capitalize on it. Rabada soon sent back Pujara and Pant to give his side a glimmer of hope. Ngidi chipped in as well with a wicket right before Lunch to make his sides job easier in the next session. The hosts would like to come back and bowl out India as soon as possible. Will India be able to stretch the lead over 200 runs? Do join us at 1610 IST (1040 GMT) to find out. Another intriguing session of Test cricket awaits.

It is time to repay the faith in the experienced pair of Rahane and Pujara. The duo racked up 66 runs in 14 overs in the first hour of the session and it looked like India will grind the hosts into dust, but the trajectory changed soon after Rahane slipped out after making his half-century. Pujara made his 32nd Test half-century but was unable to convert in into three digits. As, Pujara and Pant were sent back to the pavilion. After playing a few lusty blows Ashwin slipped out right at the brink of Lunch. But India still have a slight advantage with a lead of 161 runs.
It was certainly a session of two halves. The first one belonged to India while South Africa fought hard and made sure the visitors do not run away with the game.
A length delivery, on off and Thakur defends this solidly off the front foot onto the turf. So India are 188/6 at Lunch on Day 3. The lead for India is 161 now.

FOUR! In the air but safe! An overpitched delivery on middle. Thakur flicks this with good timing but hits it little aerially. The fielder at mid-wicket dives but the ball goes past him and Thakur gets the boundary.
Back of  a length, on off. Thakur defends this off the inside edge onto his pads.
Shardul Thakur is the new man in.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Ashwin departs now and it is one of the worst kind of dismissals for the batter. A length ball down the leg side and almost a nothing ball. Ashwin looks to clip it but gets a faint part of his blade. The ball goes behind the stumps and Kyle Verreynne moves to his left and takes an easy catch. South Africa gets another wicket and they have pulled back this game nicely now. Ashwin is a capable batter and this is a big wicket for South Africa. Can they restrict Indian lead to under 200 now?
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Lungi Ngidi

Commentary.Commentary: FOUR! DROPPED! Almost another wicket for South Africa. Back of a length, around off. Ashwin slashes this hard off the back foot this time. He gets a thick outside edge and the ball flies towards second slip. Aiden Markram jumps to catch it but fails to pouch it and the ball goes away for the boundary. Aiden Markram got his fingers there but the ball travelled quite fast off his blade.
A fuller delivery on off. Ashwin drives it straight back to the bowler.
Back of a lenth, on off. Worked to short fine leg this time.
Back of a length and angling into the body. Vihari looks to defend this off the back foot but gets beaten off the inside edge of his blade. This is the length he needs to bowl.
A short ball on off. Ashwin pulls this to deep square leg for a single this time.
FOUR! Top-class shot! Back of a length, on off. Ashwin rides the bounce and punches this off the back foot through cover-point for a boundary.
Back of a length again, around off. Ashwin looks to defend but ball zips past the outside edge of his blade.
Jansen starts with a good short delivery angling into body from 'round the wicket. Ashwin looks to defend it off the back foot and gets a top edge towards the off side.
Beaten! A good-length delivery outside off. Vihari leans forward to defend but the ball beats the outside edge of his blade as it seams away.
Back of a length on the body again. Vihari stays deep in his crease and defends it towards the on side.
Nicely played by Ashwin! A short ball on middle. Ashwin pulls it along the ground to fine leg for a single.
Back of a length on middle. Vihari goes deep in his crease and works it past short leg for a single.
Back of a length on off. Vihari works it to mid on this time.
A short ball again on middle. Ashwin pulls it to fine leg this time. He is not going to miss out on any scoring opportunity.
Rabada goes fuller this time around off. Vihari drives it without any timing towards covers.
Back of a length this time. Vihari defends it solidly off the back foot onto the turf.
A length ball, outside off. Vihari leaves it alone watchfully.
Short and down the leg side this time. Vihari looks to pull but misses.
A  length ball, on off. Ashwin drives it on up and aerially towards long off. The pair runs three this time. Good running.
Ohh...A leading edge but safe! Back of a length on middle. Ashwin looks to work it away towards the on side. But gets a leading edge towards point and the batters come back for a couple of runs.
On a length, on off. Vihari defends with soft hands and gets an outside edge to the slip corridor but along the ground.
A short ball on off. Vihari sways away from the line of the ball and looks to upper cut it but misses. Dangerous shot this under the situation.
A full ball this time on off. Vihari drives it to mid on this time. This is turning out to be an intense passage of play.
Back of a length, around off. Vihari leaves it alone.
Ohh...Another spicy delivery! A  short ball on middle and angling into body. Vihari sways away from the line of the ball.
Back of a length, around off. Vihari defends this solidly off the back foot towards the off side.
Fuller and on off. Ashwin drives it towards mid off but not in the gap.
Length ball, on the stumps. Ashwin stays inside the crease and defends it out solidly.
Good length, outside off. Ashwin looks to chase it but misses.
Ravichandran Ashwin is the next batter in.

OUT! CAUGHT! The mind game works for South Africa if there was any and Rabada strikes again. Pant fails to start the new year on a good note. He is certainly not happy with himself. A good-length ball, outside off. Pant advances down the track and looks to cut it away but misses. The ball takes the outside edge and Kyle Verreynne collects the ball with ease. Kagiso Rabada appeals and the umpire raises his finger without giving it much thought. Kagiso Rabada has got his side back in the hunt. This is the magic of Test match cricket.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: What a delivery! Back of a length, on off. This one flies off the deck. Pant stays back and looks to defend it out but gets it in front of slip cordon off the gloves. The players are being very chirpy with Pant on strike.
Swing and a miss! Good length, outside off, nipping away. Pant tries to push it away without any foot movement and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Length and on off. Vihari blocks it out solidly.
FOUR! Nicely timed! Hanuma Vihari gets his first boundary of the innings. A full-length ball, on leg. Hanuma Vihari keeps his balance and flicks it through the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone by Vihari.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Hanuma Vihari ducks under it.
Fuller, on off. Hanuma Vihari drives it with soft hands towards the bowler. Olivier gets low and stops the ball sharply.
Length and on off. Vihari blocks it out solidly.
Rishabh Pant is the next batter in.

Review! Pujara has been given out LBW here! He has reviewed it straightaway. It looks dead straight to the naked eye. The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. The Ball Tracker rolls and it shows THREE REDS. So the on-field decision stays and Pujara has to walk back.

OUT! LBW! Kagiso Rabada strikes yet again and picks up his second wicket. He has been successful in sending back the two set batters in quick succession. A full-length ball, outside off, shaping in. Pujara presses forward and looks to defend it out but gets pinged on the pads first. Kagiso Rabada appeals and the umpire raises his finger. Pujara walks across to have a chat with Vihari and takes the review. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows three reds and this is trouble for India. South Africa have a sniff now and would hope they can capitalize on it.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Hanuma Vihari gets off teh mark now! Length ball, angled into the batters. Vihari clips it towards square leg and gets off the mark.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line. Vihari shoulders his arms at it.
Full length, outside off, nipping away. Vihari prods and shoulders his arms.
Swing and a miss! Rabada draws the batter forward this time. Fuller and outside off. Vihari looks to push it to the off side but misses.
FIVE WIDES! Not the start Rabada was looking for. Back of a length, on middle. Vihari ducks under it. The ball evades the keeper's attempt and runs into the fence at fine leg.
Touch short, on the pads. Pujara clips it towards square leg for a single. Maybe this is what Rabada wanted. The new batsman on strike now.
On the pads, Puajra clips it towards deep square leg for a single.
Length and outside off. Pujara guides it towards backward point.

Review! South Africa have reviewed for an LBW against Pujara!  The replays roll in and the UltraEdge shows that no bat involved.The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the impact is outside off. So Pujara survives and the original decision stays. South Africa lose their review.

NOT OUT! Cheteshwar Pujara survies and South Africa lose a review here. Length ball, outside off, shaping in. Pujara steps across and looks to defend it out but misses and gets pinged on the pads. Duanne Olivier pleads but the umpire is unmoved. After having a chat, Dean Elgar decides to take the review. The UltraEdge confirms no bat is involved. The Ball Tracker shows the impact is outside the line and the decision cannot be overturned.
A short ball on off. Pujara sways away from the line of the ball this time.
A fuller ball on middle. Pujara defends this towards short mid-wicket this time.
A length ball, on off. Pujara defends it solidly towards the off side.
Hanuma Vihari walks in at number 5.

OUT! CAUGHT! Good pace and perfect line from Rabada gets a crucial breakthrough for his side. Back of a length, outside off. Some extra bounce off the deck. Ajinkya Rahane goes back and looks to defend it away from his body but misses. It takes the outside edge and Kyle Verreynne does the rest behind the stumps. Kagiso Rabada appeals for caught behind, the umpire takes his time and raises his dreaded finger. Rahane walks back disappointed after scoring an important fifty for his team. He would have loved to carry on but unfortunately for him Rabada has produced a beauty to get rid of him. This was the breakthrough South Africa needed.
Commentary.Howout: c Kyle Verreynne b Kagiso Rabada

Commentary.Commentary: Back of a length, outside off. Rahane shuffles across and leaves it alone for the keeper.
Good length, on off. Rahane defends it to the on side off the inner half.
Length ball, on off. Rahane remains solid in his defense.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
It looks like Jansen has hurt himself near the fence while stopping the boundary. He is fine now and ready to resume.

FOUR! Through the gap! A full-length ball, on off. Rahane stays back and drives it through covers. Marco Jansen gives it a chase and does well to keep the ball in play, as he goes on the floor beyond the rope. Temba Bavuma runs in and collects the ball to keep it down to three runs. Oh wait! The replays show Bavuma had his foot on the outline of the crease and hence in a boundary.

Drinks! What a counter-attacking partnership this has been between the senior duo of Pujara and Rahane. They have stepped up just when their team needed it the most. South African bowlers have leaked far too many runs in this first hour and they need some quick wickets now to get back into this game. We have seen wickets falling in the last hour of the first session in the first two days and South Africa will be hoping that same happens in the next hour of play.
Good length, on off. Pujara hangs back and defends it out watchfully.
Full-length ball, outside off. This one bounces off the deck. Pujara shuffles across and shoulders his arms at it.
Quick single! On the pads, tucked to mid-wicket for a single.

BYE! Misses everyone! A length ball, sliding down leg. Pujara looks to flick it away but misses. Kyle Verreynne dives to his left but the ball evades him. The batters collect a bye. 150 now up for India.
A sharp bouncer, on middle. Pujara sits under it and leaves it alone.
Length ball, on leg. Rahane nudges it to square leg and gets across for a single. First runs after 9 balls for India.
Outside off, Pujara has no stroke to offer.
Good length, on the fourth stump line. This one flies off the deck. Pujara shoulders his arms at it and Kyle Verreynne gathers it above his head.
Does not carry! Back of a length, on off. Pujara hops inside the crease and defends it to short leg off his gloves. Luckily for Pujara, the ball lands short of the man placed there.
Fuller and on off. Pujara stays back and defends it to covers watchfully.
Short ball, on off. Pujara sways away from the line of the delivery.

Past the outside edge! Shout from some South Africans but the umpire is unmoved. A length ball, outside off, shaping away. Pujara presses forward as he looks to defend it out but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
On a length, just outside off. The ball hits the crack on the deck and nips in a bit. Rahane hangs back and defends it out solidly.
Back of a length, outside off. Rahane leaves it alone for the keeper.
Outside off, left alone.

FOUR! Ajinkya Rahane reads the delivery really well and gets his FIFTY in some fine fashion. Back of a length, on off. Rahane leans back and plays the ramp shot to guide it towards third man and finds a boundary.

FOUR! Top placement! Rahane used the extra pace here. Good length, outside off. Rahane opens the face of the blade and steers it through the gap between backward point and gully for a boundary. The stand moves over 100 runs now.
Short ball, sliding down leg at a rapid pace. Rahane looks to pull it away but misses. The keeper moves to his left to gather the ball.
Short ball, on off. Pujara ducks it under without any hesitation.
Swing and a miss now! A beautiful delivery from Kagiso Rabada. A length ball, in the corridor of uncertainty. Pujara looks to play away from his body but misses and gets beaten on the outside edge.
Good length, sliding down leg. Pujara leaves it alone for the keeper.
Length ball, on the stumps. Pujara stays back and blocks it out.
Short ball, on off. Pujara ducks under it. Rabada has overstepped and the umpire signals a no ball.
Rahane has ben hit on his finger while playing a defensive shot! He is getting some treatment now and looks fine to resume.

EDGY! The gully fielder and the man at second slip both left the catch for each other and in the end, the ball lands safely. Ajinkya Rahane riding his luck here. Back of a length, around off. This one flies off the deck. Rahane stays inside the crease and looks to defend it out. The ball hits him on the gloves and balloons towards the right to the second slip fielder. Aiden Markram was going for it but he thought Keegan Petersen is going for it and stops his runs towards the ball. No one gets there and Rahane gets across for a single.
Good length, on the pads. Rahane stays back and flicks it to deep square leg for a single.

Fifty for Pujara in just 62 balls! This has been a fine innings from the fine player! He was playing for his place in the side and he delivers just when his team needed it the most. A length ball on middle. Pujara tucks it towards square leg and gets a single. Superb knock by the the number 3 batter and he will surely want to convert this one into a big hundred.
A good-length delivery outside off. Pujara leaves it alone.
Back of a length, on middle. Rahane tucks it behind square on the on side for a single.

Ohh..That has taken off! Duanne Olivier bowls this on a length and that hits the crack and bounce off sharply. Rahane tries to defend it initially but then sways away from the line of the ball. Good leave.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahane leaves it alone watchfully.
Back of a length around leg. Pujara works it behind square on the on side for a single.
Duanne Olivier comes into the attack now.
Short and down the leg side this time. Rahane lets it go.
Another shorter length delivery on off. Rahane goes back and defends it off the backfoot again.
Back of a length, on off. Solidly defended off the back foot.
FOUR! Rahane gets another boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Rahane defends this with soft hand and gets the outside edge of his blade. The ball flies through slip corridor for a boundary.
On a length, on off. Rahane defends this off the front foot with soft hands.

FOUR BYES! A nasty short ball but it has beaten everyone. A good short ball on middle. Rahane looks to hook it but misses. Kyle Verreynne behind the stumps misses it too and the ball races away for the boundary. The lead is over 100 now.
A full delivery on off to finish the over. Rahane drives it wide of mid off and gets a single.
Ngidi bowls this on a good length, outside off. Rahane leaves it watchfully.
On a length, on off. Rahane solidly defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
A fuller ball, on middle. Rahane clips it to mid-wicket. The fielder there misfields and the batters get a couple of runs.
On a length and angling into middle. Pujara defends this off the outer half of his blade towards covers for a quick single.
On a good length around off. Pujara defends this off the front foot onto the turf.
Back of a length, on off. Rahane swivels and looks to pull it away and gets hit on his body. This must've hurt a bit.
Another slightly shorter length delivery on off. Rahane rides the bounce and defends it towards the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Rahane solidly defends this towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahane leaves it alone.
Back of a length, around leg. Rahane looks to work it away but misses.
FOUR! Another boundary! Back of a length, outside off. Rahane punches this off the back foot through point for another boundary.
NO BALL! Back of a length on off that bounces off sharply on off. Rahane defends this off the back foot. Rabada has overstepped here.

FOUR! Soft hands by Pujara! A good-length delivery around off. Pujara gets forward and looks to defend the ball finds the outside edge of his blade and flies wide of the second slip fielder along the ground for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Pujara defends this solidly off the back foot onto the turf.
On a length and nipping in from around off this time. Rahane looks to defend this off the front foot but gets the inside half of his blade. The ball goes behind square on the on side for a single.
Ngidi goes touch wider and bowls this fuller outside off again. Rahane leaves it alone.
A fuller delivery on off. Rahane defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
FOUR! Rahane is showing his class here! That's a decent delivery on a good-length outside off. Rahane cuts it touch aerially wide of gully for another boundary.
A good-length ball, outside off. Pujara lets it go this time. Perfect start for India.
A short ball on off this time. Rahane pulls this to deep square leg for a single.
SIX! Fantastic shot by Rahane! Short and wide outside off by Jansen Rahane picks the length quickly and cuts it over point for a maximum. This has  been a brilliant start for India.
A short ball and down the leg side this time. Rahane ducks under it.
A length ball, on off this time. Rahane gets the inside edge onto his pads this time as he looks to defend.
A full and hint of in swing there. This is around leg and Rahane looks to clip it but misses. Gets hit on the pads but it is down the leg side.
This is the length where they need to be!  A good-length delivery on off. Pujara is well forward to defend it.
An overpitched ball, on off. Pujara drives it straight to mid off this time.
Full length, on off. Pujara pushes it back to the bowler with soft hands.
Back of a length, around off. Pujara defends it towards gully.
Good-length ball, outside off. Pujara punches it hard towards point. The fielder there does well to make the stop.

Big shout from South Africa but the umpire is unmoved! A good-length delivery on off and nips back in sharply. Pujara looks to defend but misses and gets rapped up on the pads. There is a huge appeal but the umpire says no. Dean Elgar decides to not review it. The replays later show that the ball was going way above the stumps. A good decision by Dean Elgar to opt against the review.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rahane leaves it alone comfortably.
Jansen pulls his length back and bowls this around off. Rahane defends this off the back foot towards the off side.
FOUR! Sublime timing by Rahane and what a way to bring out the hundred for the team! A full ball, on off. Rahane leans forward and drives it straight back past the bowler for a lovely boundary.
Back of a length, around leg this time. Rahane works it to fine leg for a couple.
Length ball, angling down leg. Rahane stays back and looks to flick it but misses. The ball was very close to the blade. The bowler and the keeper make a stifled appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
Back of a length, on off. Rahane rides the bounce and pushes it to square on the off side.
Back of a length, on off. Pujara rides the bounce and pushes it to covers.
On a length and nipping in a little from off. Pujara defends it off the inside half of his blade towards the on side.
Ngidi pulls his length back a little, around off. Pujara leaves it alone.

FOUR! Another boundary for Pujara and he is looking in good touch here. A full ball, on off. Pujara quickly picks the length and drives it through mid on for another boundary. The stand moves to 51 runs.
A good-length delivery outside off. Pujara leaves it alone this time.
FOUR! Pujara continues from where he left off! A full ball and down the leg side. Pujara clips it fine to long leg for a boundary. Positive start for India.
Lungi Ngidi to steam in from the other end.
Back of a length around off. Rahane looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pads. Good confident start by Rahane.
Good-length delivery outside off. Rahane lets it go this time.
Shorter length on off. Rahane pulls it to deep mid-wicket and gets a couple. First runs of the day for Rahane and India.
A full ball, on off this time. Rahane pushes this towards the off side and wants a single but is sent back by his partner.
Jansen pulls his length back a little this time. It is around off and Rahane leaves it alone.
Jansen starts with a full-length delivery on off. Rahane defends this off the front foot towards the off side solidly.

The first session is set to begin. The South African players stride out to the middle. Followed by Cheteshwar Pujara and Ajinkya Rahane who walk out to bat for India. Marco Jansen to start with the ball.

Lungi Ngidi is in for a chat. He says, he is all good other than a pair of stiff legs. Mentions, the ball does a lot on this deck. If you pitch on the fourth stump line, the ball nips away both the side. Adds, he tries to keep it simple. Adds, the group needs to be a lot more disciplined and stick to the basics and keep the batters in check.

Pitch Report - Morne Morkel says that there are cracks on the pitch and they will open up. He adds that the wicket does look drier and it will turn. He mentions that it will be tough wicket to bat and if bowlers bowl in good areas they will get rewards on this wicket.

Shardul Thakur was the star for India on Day 2 as he picked seven wickets to restrict South Africa to 229. South Africa still managed to get a crucial lead of 27 runs and have priced out both the Indian openers before the end of play on Day 2. However, India have a lead of 58 runs now with eight wickets in hand and given that South Africa have to bat last on this pitch, the pressure is on South Africa to restrict India to a low total here. Can India set a formidable target for South Africa to chase? Or will South African bowlers dominate the proceedings and bundle out India quickly today? A riveting day of Test cricket coming up.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 3 of the second Test match between South Africa and India. This Test match has moved at a rapid pace so far with 22 wickets falling in the first two days and the third day could well turn out to be the deciding day of this Test match. The match hangs right in the balance at this point in time and it will be interesting to see who will inch ahead at the end of Day 3.
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 …

Right then, India lead by 58 runs at the end of Day 2 with 8 wickets in hand. Can they set a formidable target for South Africa on Day 3? We are in for a riveting day of Test cricket on the third day of this Test match. The action begins at 1.30 pm IST (8.00 am GMT) but our coverage will start well in advance. Do join us for that. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Earlier in the day, it was Lord Thakur show as he picked seven wickets to bundle out South Africa for 229. South African batters, on the other hand, did well to get a crucial lead of 27 runs but they have to bat last on this pitch and that can be difficult task on this pitch. So it is upto their bowlers now to restrict India to as low a total as possible. But the game stands well in balance at this point of time.

South African bowlers bowled with good steam and troubled Indian batters quite a lot. The youngster Jansen again provided the first breakthrough as he got the big fish Rahul out cheaply. The comeback man, Duanne Olivier got the wicket of Mayank Agarwal as both the in-form batters were sent back to the hut. They have already got two wickets and will be looking to get eight more as early as possible on Day 3 to restrict India to a chaseable total here.

Indian batters showed good intent and did not miss out on any scoring opportunity. But the wickets of their two in-form batters have pulled them back a little. The experienced duo of Pujara and Rahane is out there in the middle and India will hope that they finally deliver when it matters the most. Pujara has batted with good positive intent so far in this innings. Remember, they are also playing for their place in the team and it will be interesting to see how they go about their business on Day 3.

FOUR! Cheteshwar Pujara ends the day with a boundary. Was a little bit streaky but he won't mind it. Loopy ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara presses forward and looks to defend. The ball goes off the outside edge past the slip fielder to third man for a boundary. THAT WILL BE STUMPS ON DAY 2! India lead by 58 runs!
Outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Drops it short and outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara hangs back and pounces on that one. Cuts it past cover-point for a boundary.
Tossed up, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara presses forward and defends it out.
Keshav Maharaj will bowl the last over of the day.
Full and on middle, Cheteshwar Pujara advances and pushes it to mid on.
Loopy ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara hangs back and defends it to the off side.
On the pads, clipped behind square on the leg side for one.
Fuller, on middle. Pushed to mid on.
Good-length ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it out.
On middle. Cheteshwar Pujara looks to flick but misses. He gets hit on the pads. An appeal for an lbw but the umpire says no.
On a good length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Length ball, on middle and leg. Ajinkya Rahane glances it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, outside off. Ajinkya Rahane dabs it to gully. No ball called for overstepping.
FOUR! Aggressive batting this! Full again, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara this time pushes it to long on for a boundary. South Africa are leaking runs here on the back-end of Day 2!
Bangs a short ball, on middle. Cheteshwar Pujara ducks under it.
Angling in a length ball, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara shoulders arms.
Full again, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara drives it to extra cover this time.
FOUR! Top batting! Fuller in length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara steers it past point for a boundary.
Back of a length, on off. Ajinkya Rahane taps it towards covers for a quick single.
Fuller in length, outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
That has hit Cheteshwar Pujara on the thigh pad as he looks to flick this length ball.
Back of a length, on off. Cheteshwar Pujara blocks it out. That took off after landing but Pujara does well to negotiate it.
On middle and leg, tucked on the leg side for a single.
Jaffa! Good-length ball, outside off, shaping away. Ajinkya Rahane hops and looks to defend. The ball whizzes past the outside edge. Too good a delivery that.

Right then! That is it from the coverage of this enthralling Test at Wanderers. The series is levelled at 1-1 and the action now shifts to Newlands, Cape Town for the final and the deciding Test match of this series. It will commence on 11th January, 2022. Day 1 of this Test will begin at 2 pm IST (8.30 am GMT). But as all of you are aware, the buildup will begin well in advance and make sure you join us for the same. Till then, cheers and take care!

Dean Elgar, the South African skipper is the PLAYER OF THE MATCH for his brilliant performance with the bat. He says that there is no wrong or right way to win the game. He adds that the fundamentals of the game are important and they lacked that in the last game and this win was tough as they did the fundamentals right here. He mentions that bowlers showed a lot of character to get 20 wickets on this pitch. He mentions that it is his privilege to represent the country. He adds that his knocks can be ugly for some but it is okay to take blows and the bigger picture is to win the game of cricket. He adds that a lot of testimony should go to batters as have been preparing to build this batting unit for a long time. The conditions were difficult and he is glad that they won. Tells that Rassie van der Dussen's 40 will go a long way in his career and he showed a lot of character. He adds that they had a talk with Rabada in the dressing room and he has that attitude and fire to perform and overall it’s a team effort and getting 20 wickets is not easy. He adds that he is not sure how Cape Town surface will be and mentions that Newlands, Cape Town is his favourite ground in the world.

KL Rahul, the skipper of India, says that they wanted to win and they always want to play a good brand of cricket. Adds that he is a bit disappointed but credits South Africa for the way they batted and bowled. Tells that getting 122 on Day 4 wasn't going to be easy but the South African batters played really well. Mentions that they could have batted slightly better in the first innings and got 50-60 runs more. Adds that Shardul Thakur had a great Test match and he bowled and batted really well. Talking about Ajinkya Rahane and Cheteshwar Pujara, Rahul says that they both are world-class batters and they had team's backing. Says that Virat should be fine for the next game as he has batted a bit in the nets and has also been running around on the field. Tells that they will monitor Siraj for the next game and hopefully he will be fine for the last Test.
Stay tuned for the presentation.

The pitch at Wanderers is expected to be tricky for the batters and we witnessed that right from Day 1 as the South African bowlers dominated the proceedings and bundled out India for 202 in the first innings. The youngster, Marco Jansen was the pick of the bowlers with four wickets while it was Lord Shardul Thakur who ruled Day 2 as he picked seven wickets to restrict South Africa to 229. South Africa still managed a lead of 27 runs with useful fifties from Keegan Petersen and Bavuma. India needed their experienced duo of Pujara and Rahane to fire on Day 3 and they delivered with counter-attacking fifties and South Africa were eventually set a target of 240 to win this game. In the end, some astute batting by South Africa, led by their skipper, took them home in a tricky chase and this is a big win for this South African team that is trying to build towards a new era in their Test cricket history.

India needed 8 wickets this morning and with this pitch known to produce wickets in a cluster, India were in with a good chance. But the South African batters batted positively and never let the Indian bowlers settle. Shami did get the wicket of Rassie van der Dussen but India were denied any further breakthrough and they have finally lost a Test match at Wanderers. India will have to wait for Cape Town for their first-ever Test series victory in the rainbow nation.

South African batters showed great application on the pitch that had enough help for the bowlers to trouble the batters regularly. It was their skipper, Dean Elgar who led from the front and some useful contributions from other top-order batters have taken them to a rather comfortable victory on Day 4 here. Quite fittingly, it was the experienced pair of Elgar and Bavuma who finished things off for South Africa. This means a lot to South African cricket.

What a fascinating Test match this has been as momentum kept tilting from one team to another and finally, South Africa have trumped India to level the series here at Wanderers. They win by 7 wickets and have beaten India at the Wanderers in Test cricket for the first time.

DRINKS BREAK. Well, a look at the scorecard and you would say that South Africa are cruising. But if you have actually followed the game in the last 30 minutes or so, you would feel that anything is possible even now. India started the day poorly, giving too many freebies but the last 30 minutes have seen them getting disciplined. That resulted in the wicket of Rassie van der Dussen and almost of Bavuma too. Sunil Gavaskar on air opines that he sees players practice those tough boundary catches in warmup sessions but no fast bowler practices return catches. Adds that those must be practiced too. 59 runs needed for one team, 7 wickets required for the other. Trust us - this is not over yet. Play can technically go on till 10 pm IST (1630 GMT) but the conditions are already murky and the floodlights are switched on. Don't see this going for too long.

DROPPED! Heart-in-mouth moment for India and South Africa. But cannot blame the bowler here. Such catches either stick or they don't. Full, around off, Temba Bavuma looked to drive straight. But the ball hit a patch of grass and bounced a tad extra. Hence, it hit the higher part of the bat. As a result, Bavuma was unable to control the shot and spooned it straight back. Now, Thakur is a right-arm fast bowler and when he is running from over the wicket, the momentum takes him to the left. But the ball comes to his right. Thakur realizes it but perhaps goes a bit too early, being a bit too anxious. He maybe, anticipated the ball to come quickly but it came a tad slower. He stuck his right hand out but the ball hit his palm and dropped down.

On a length, just short of full, outside off, Rassie van der Dussen plays at it tentatively. He is neither forward nor back and pushes at it. The ball comes in with the angle but after pitching, the ball moves away late. That squares van der Dussen up and he tries his best to follow the ball. But all he can manage is an outside edge, which goes straight into the hands of Cheteshwar Pujara at first slip. The game opens again. South Africa need 65 runs. India need 7 wickets. Game on.

On a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen blocks it out.

Full ball, outside off. Dean Elgar presses forward to defend but it goes off the outer half of the blade towards backward point.
Length ball, just outside off. Rassie van der Dussen prods to block but the ball takes from a length and hits him high on his blade.
Thakur goes fuller and wider, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen lets it through to the keeper.
Short of a length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen shoulders arms to this one.
On a length, way outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Length ball, outside off and curling away late. Rassie van der Dussen presses forward to defend but the ball zips past his outside edge.

A loud shout for LBW but the umpire is not interested! Good-length ball, jagging back in from outside off and taking off from a length. Rassie van der Dussen prods to block but he misses and gets hit high on his pad.
Another delivery, on a length and nipping back in from outside off. Dean Elgar gets behind the line of the ball to block it.
Short of a length, jagging back in from off. Dean Elgar gets on top of the bounce and defends it on the leg side.
On a length, angling in from off. Rassie van der Dussen looks to block but it goes off the thick inside edge towards fine leg for a run.
BEATEN! Good-length ball, just outside off and shaping away a bit. Rassie van der Dussen prods to defend but it whistles past his outside edge. Lovely delivery from Shami!
Back of a length, nipping back in sharply. Rassie van der Dussen hangs back and pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball, jagging back in from middle. Dean Elgar turns it towards mid-wicket and takes a quick run.

FOUR! What a shot! This was slightly shorter in length, outside off. Rassie van der Dussen stands tall, rides the bounce nicely and punches it through the cover region for a boundary. Runs are coming thick and fast for the hosts!
Good-length ball, around leg. Dean Elgar nudges it towards deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, around off and bouncing sharply off a length. Rassie van der Dussen looks to block but it goes off the inside half of the blade towards square leg for a run.

FOUR! Edgy! Back of a length, just outside off and curling away late. Rassie van der Dussen looks to drive on the up but it goes off the outside edge past the slip cordon and into the fence. Had there been a gully in place, it would have been straight to him.
Good-length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Rassie van der Dussen stays back and defends it to the off side.
Thakur starts with a length ball, down leg. Dean Elgar glances it towards fine leg and collects a run.
Shardul Thakur (9.0-1-24-1) is back into the attack now.
A good-length delivery outside off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone watchfully. An expensive over from Shami and South Africa are right on the top now.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the back foot solidly.
A fuller delivery on off. Rassie van der Dussen drives it to point.

FOUR! Rassie van der Dussen is turning the heat on! A quick bouncer on off by Shami. Rassie van der Dussen hangs back and pulls this in front of square for another boundary.
FOUR! Another boundary and pressure is building on India now! A fuller delivery on middle and leg. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and flicks it through square leg for a boundary.

Ohh.. Bumrah is quite consistently hitting that area near the crack. He bowls this on a good-length around off. The ball nips in sharply with extra bounce and Rassie van der Dussen gets the inside edge onto his pads as looks to clip it.
Slight halt in play as the umpires are having a close look at the ball and they have decided to change it finally as it has got too wet!

FOUR! Classy shot by Rassie van der Dussen! Slightly overpitched on off. Rassie van der Dussen leans forward and drives it crisply off the middle of his blade through covers for a lovely boundary. South Africa need just 93 runs now. India need wickets quickly here.
Bumrah bowls this on a crack around good-length. Rassie van der Dussen looks to flick it but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
A good-length delivery around off and seaming into the batter. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone.
On a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the front foot towards the off side.
Back of a length, around off. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it alone comfortably.
Shami beats him all ends up this time! A good-length delivery around off from 'round the wicket. The ball first comes in with the angle and then seams away to beat Elgar who tries to defend it.
Back of a length, on off. Rassie van der Dussen rides the bounce and punches it to covers for a single. Fifty partnership between these two. Crucial one in the context of the game.
KL Rahul has a chat with the umpire and he is not happy with the condition of the ball. He asks for a replacement but the umpire does not agree!
Drifting on the pads and a easy single given to Elgar. He clips it to deep square leg for a single.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it comfortably.
Shami pulls his length back a little and bowls this around off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.

This one bounces sharply off a length. On a length on off. This one nips in and hits him high on the pads as he tries to defend it.
Ohhh...This one is in that channel around off and seams in. Rassie van der Dussen leaves it and thankfully for him it dosen't strike the off stump.
On a good-length on off. Rassie van der Dussen works it away towards the on side.
Another length delivery on off. Elgar defends it solidly again.
On a length, on off and coming in with the angle from 'round the wicket. Elgar defends it from his crease.
Shami goes short this time and bowls this on middle. Elgar ducks under it. There is definite ploy of bowling short and then going fuller.
A good-length delivery around off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Shami pulls his length back a little on off. Elgar defends this off the back foot onto the turf.
On a length from 'round the wicket angling into the stumps. Elgar defends it towards mid on.
Mohammed Shami is on now! There is also a drizzle now. The players though are still out there.
Solid! On off, blocked again. End of an action-packed over.
Going down leg! Angled into the pads, Rassie looks to flick but misses! It hits the pad, a huge appeal but turned down. That is going down leg.

Well defended! Good length and on off, this lands and takes off, Rassie defends with one hand off the handle.
Well left! This lands outside off, extra bounce. Rassie watches it closely and leaves it alone.
Angled into the pads, Rassie works it to mid-wicket.
Very full again by Ashwin on middle. Elgar flicks it to mid-wicket.

Flatter on middle. Defended by Elgar off the back foot.

A fuller delivery on middle. Worked to mid-wicket this time.

On a length, on off and seaming away a little. Rassie van der Dussen defends this towards gully.

India, on the other hand, are on the cusp of making history and this Indian team have snatched victory with their spirited performance on the day it matters the most quite a few times in the recent past. Can they create history by winning their first-ever Test series in the rainbow nation? Or will South Africa level the series? A critical first session coming up.

Hello and a warm welcome to Day 4 of this second Test match between South Africa and India. The equation is quite simple, India need another 8 wickets to win while South Africa need 122 runs to win this game. The match is right in the balance or one could say, slightly towards South Africa but the first hour is an important one and could define which way the game will go.
... DAY 4, SESSION 1 …

Right then, Day 4 most probably will be the last day of this Test match. Both teams will fancy their chances of winning this one and we can expect some intense and quality Test cricket as both these teams fight it out. Can India register their first-ever Test series victory on South African soil? Or will Proteas level the series with a spirited chase here? Do join us to find out. The action starts at 1.30 pm IST (8.00 am GMT) but our coverage begins well in advance. Till then, goodbye and cheers!

Earlier in the day, India riding on the twin fifties of Pujara and Rahane managed to set a target of 240 for South Africa. Rabada was impressive as he broke the backbone of the Indian middle-order with the wickets of Rahane, Pujara and Pant. But such has been the spirit of this Indian team that Vihari along with the lower order managed to take them to a formidable total. Now after yet another riveting day of Test cricket, we can still say that this match hangs right in the balance.

It was Lord Shardul Thakur who started the session with a brilliant spell and got rid of Aiden Markram. All other bowlers were quite disciplined but the breakthrough eluded them as Elgar and Keegan Petersen started building a solid partnership. But this is a Test match and you cannot keep Ashwin out of the action for long and he delivered yet again with a wicket of solid-looking Keegan Petersen. Indian bowlers failed to get any further breakthrough and will now need 8 wickets to seal this match and series on Day 4.

South Africa need 122 runs to win and have 8 wickets in hand. Captain Elgar is looking solid out there in the middle and has Rassie van der Dussen for his company. Aiden Markram and Keegan Petersen made good starts to their innings but failed to kick on. South Africa will hope that this pair continues their good work in the first session on Day 4 and if they do that South Africa are in with a great chance to win this one.

Good length, angled across the left-hander, on off. Elgar defends it out off the bottom end of his blade.
Nicely tossed up on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends it off the front foot. Ashwin is all over Rassie van der Dussen here and has Pant for his support with some quite funny and sarcastic talks.
A flatter ball on off. Rassie van der Dussen defends it square on the off side.
A full ball and Rassie van der Dussen defends this off the back foot. Almost got him there Ashwin. Pant is having fun behind the stumps.
A shorter length delivery on middle. Rassie van der Dussen somehow manages to work it towards short leg.
Drifting on the pads and Elgar tucks it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Nice drift there for Ashwin. He bowls this around off. Rassie van der Dussen gets back and plays it late behind square on the off side for a single.
Back of a length around leg. Rassie van der Dussen pulls it to fine leg for a single. Ashwin will now get the chance to bowl at Rassie van der Dussen.
Bumrah goes fuller and Elgar drives it through covers. Ashwin chases it and cuts it off. Three runs taken by the batters.
An effort ball from Bumrah. He bowls this short on middle. Elgar ducks under it rather comfortably.
Ohhh... In that channel around off. Dean Elgar decides to let it go.
Bumrah bowls this shorter on off. Elgar is solid in his defence.
Bumrah bowls this on a good length outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Quicker and flatter delivery on off. Defended off the back foot this time. End of a brilliant over by Ashwin.
Tossed up on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends but gets the inside edge on his blade and ball falls just short of Pujara at leg slip.
Slower in the air on middle. Rassie van der Dussen defends it towards short leg this time.
A flatter ball on middle. Defended off the back foot.
Rassie van der Dussen is the new man in.

OUT! LBW! Ravichandran Ashwin strikes! This is a huge wicket for India. This partnership was looking quite threatening and Ashwin provides the crucial breakthrough! Slightly shorter delivery on middle and turning in. Keegan Petersen looks to clip this off the back foot but misses. The ball hits his pads and there is a huge appeal. The umpire raises his finger and Ravichandran Ashwin is elated. Keegan Petersen has a chat with Elgar and decides against taking a review. So India have finally got the second wicket and can they capitalise on this breakthrough now?
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: A fuller ball on middle. Defended solidly back to the bowler.
Siraj goes fuller this time outside off. Elgar resists driving and lets it go.
Good-length delivery around off. Elgar is in no mood to play that one.
A short ball on middle by Siraj. Elgar carefully ducks under it.
Siraj pulls his length back a little this time and bowls this on middle. Keegan Petersen works it to deep square leg for just a single this time.
Siraj goes fuller this time on middle. Keegan Petersen drives this off the inside half of his balde and gets it to deep square leg for a couple.
Back of a length around leg. Keegan Petersen looks to clip it but misses. He gets hit high on the pads but no damage done.
A flatter and quicker delivery on off. Defended off the front foot solidly.
Ashwin tosses this up around off. Elgar leaves it alone.
A fuller delivery on middle. Worked to mid-wicket this time.
Fuller this time on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot.
Shorter again on off. Keegan Petersen cuts it to point for a single this time.
Shorter and flatter by Ashwin on off. Keegan Petersen blocks this off the back foot.
In that channel around off. Elgar watchfully lets it go again.
Siraj goes fuller and wider outside off. Elgar is not interested in playing that one.
Another length delivery around off by Siraj. Elgar carefully lets it go.
A good-length delivery, angling away from the batter. Elgar leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen rides the bounce and punches it to deep cover for a single.
Back of a length and angling into the body. Keegan Petersen looks to defend but gets hit high on his pads.

DRINKS! South Africa have scored at a really good pace here. After losing Aiden Markram it looked as if the India bowlers would be able to put a lid over the run rate but Keegan Petersen have settled in really fast to support Dean Elgar in the middle. The hosts would hope the pair continues on their merry way till the remaining passage of play. India, on the flip side, know one wicket can change the trajectory of the game and will like to break this partnership which might hurt them a lot.
Tossed up again, around off. Elgar leaves it alone as it turns away sharply. Elgar is a key man here for South Africa.
Nicely tossed up on off. Elgar defends it off the front foot this time.
A fuller ball on off. Elgar defends it watchfully back to the bowler.
A flatter ball, outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
A fuller ball on leg and turning in. Keegan Petersen looks to flick it but misses. Pant fails to collect it cleanly and a bye is taken behind him.
Ashwin drifting on the pads. Elgar clips it through square leg for a single.
Back of a length to end the over on off. Keegan Petersen solidly defends it.
A good-length delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
This one nips in sharply! A good-length delivery around off. Keegan Petersen leaves it but the ball jags back in sharply and goes just over the off pole.
Back of a length and down the leg side this time. Keegan Petersen looks to clip it but misses.
FOUR! Keegan Petersen is on the attack and he has smashed this short ball! A short ball on off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary.
Siraj bowls this on a good length around off. Keegan Petersen lets it go as it nips into him.
On the pads, Elgar nudges it towards square leg. A probing over by Ashwin. Some bounce and turn in his first over. Good signs for the spinner.
Nice turn! Tossed up, full and on off. Elgar is drawn forward to defend it out but gets beaten by the away turn.
Around off, Elgar blocks it watchfully.
A brace now! Floated, full and on off. Elgar leans forward to defend it out and does so with the outside edge. The ball goes towards third man and the batters run two.
Short and outside off, turning in. Keegan Petersen stays back and cuts it through point for a single.
Tossed up, outside off. Keegan Petersen shuffles across and blocks it towards cover.
Ravichandran Ashwin is into the attack.
Just two runs off the over! A good over by Shami. Full length, on off. Elgar defends it towards mid off.
Full and on off. Elgar blocks it back to the bowler on a bounce.
Good length, on off. Elgar blocks it out watchfully.
On a length, outside off. Elgar guides it past the man at gully for a couple of runs.
Length and on off, blocked out solidly.
Fuller and on off. Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Good length, on top of off. Keegan Petersen steers it towards third man for a brace.
Around the hips, Elgar stays back and tucks it to deep square leg for a single this time.
Outside off, Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, on off. Elgar defends it out solidly.
Short and outside off. Petersen works it towards point for a single.
Short and outside off. Tapped through point for a brace.
Mohammed Siraj is into the attack now.

Second maiden of the innings for Shami. A great over by the seamer, asking plenty of questions. A length ball, angled into the pads. Elgar presses forward to defend it out but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
Five dots on the trot! Very full and on off. Elgar defends it into the deck.
Short ball, outside off. Elgar hangs his blade away from his body and gets beaten.
Full length, on off. Elgar defends it back to the bowler.
Outside off, shaping away with some extra bounce. Elgar was caught in two minds but in the end he decides to leave it alone.
A sharp bouncer, wide outside off. Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Three dots in a row to end the over for Shardul Thakur. Fuller, on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen stays back and clips it towards short mid-wicket. Not in the gap though.
Fuller, on leg. Keegan Petersen flicks it towards mid-wicket. Cheteshwar Pujara gets low to his left to make the stop.
What a delivery! Short ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen looks to defend it out but pulls his blade back in time.
FOUR! Played it late and gets a boundary. Length and outside off. Keegan Petersen opens the face of the bat really late and steers it towards third man for a boundary.
Length, on the pads. Elgar flicks it towards square leg for a single.

BEATEN! Shardul Thakur steams in from 'round the wicket. Good length ball, outside off. This one nips away off the deck. Elgar presses forward and looks to drive it towards cover but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Back of a length, on off. Keegan Petersen defends this solidly yet again. Keegan Petersen is looking solid and has grown in confidence after the fifty in the first innings.
This one keeps low. Second of the innings! A length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen defends this off the bottom of his blade.
On a length, on off. Elgar defends it with soft hands towards the off side and takes a quick single.
Back of a length, around off. Elgar leaves it alone this time.
FOUR! Nice little punch by Elgar! A full ball on middle. Elgar waits for it and then clips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Good shot!
Shami bowls this on a length, outside off. Elgar decides to leave it alone.
That's a good leave! A good-length delivery around off. Keegan Petersen carefully lets it go.
A length ball on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen works it away wide of mid on.
Another fuller delivery on off this time Keegan Petersen pushes it to mid on.
Thakur goes little fuller this time on off. Keegan Petersen is solid in his front foot defence.
He hits the length hard and bowls this one on off. Elgar works it towards the on side for a single.
A length ball, on off. Elgar defends this off the front foot towards mid on.
Shami goes fuller this time on off. Keegan Petersen lets it swing away and then pushes it to point.
Back of a length on off. Keegan Petersen blocks it solidly towards the off side.
On a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone again.
A good-length delivery around off and this one nips away from the batter. Keegan Petersen lets it go.
Ohh..This one nips into the batter sharply! A good-length ball on off and nips back in. Keegan Petersen looks to defend but gets the inside edge onto his pads. He nearly drags it back to the stumps.
Shami is right on the target straightaway! A good-length delivery on off. Keegan Petersen defends it solidly back to the bowler.
A full ball again on off. Elgar drives it to mid off this time.
Thakur beats the blade of Elgar yet again! A fuller delivery around off. Elgar looks to drive but gets beaten off the outside edge of his blade. This has been a fantastic spell by Thakur.
Back of a length on off. Keegan Petersen defends it with soft hands towards the off side and takes a quick single.
Another length delivery around leg. Elgar works it to fine leg for a single.
A length ball and down the leg side. Elgar looks to clip it but misses.
Thakur goes fuller on off. Elgar drives it back to the bowler.
On the stumps this time and again that shorter length. Elgar works it away behind square on the on side as his one hand comes off the handle. A single taken.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar defends it square on the off side.
A short ball and angling into body from 'round the wicket. Elgar ducks under it.
Back of a length on the pads. Keegan Petersen looks to clip it but misses. Gets hit on the thigh pad and ball rolls behind square on the on side. A leg bye taken.
Bumrah pulls his length back a little and bowls this around off. Keegan Petersen blocks this off the back foot towards the off side.
FOUR! Keegan Petersen plays another lovely shot! A full ball on middle by Bumrah. Keegan Petersen leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.

A huge appeal for caught behind but the umpire is unmoved! Some noise there but not off the blade. Thakur has been exception in the Test match with the ball. He gets his first maiden of this innings. He has asked a lot of questions since the last two overs. Good length, outside off, shaping away. Elgar looks to have a poke at it but misses.
Past the outside edge! Good length, shaping across the batter. Elgar looks to play at it but gets beaten on the outside edge..
Fuller, on middle and leg. Elgar blocks it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! A length ball, angled across the left-hander. Elgar comes forward and looks to push it to the off side but misses. The ball zips past the outside edge.
Fuller and outside off. Elgar blocks it out safely.
Length and on off, defended out solidly.
FOUR! Glorious shot! Fuller and outside off. Keegan Petersen leans in and creams it through the cover region for a boundary. A good end to the over for South Africa.
OUCH! A length ball, around off. This one flies off the deck. Keegan Petersen misses his attempt to defend it out and gets hit near the ribs.
BEATEN! This has come back a long way. On a length, outside off, nips in off the deck. Keegan Petersen looks to push it away from his body but misses.
A single now! Fuller, outside off. Elgar works it to covers for a quick single.
Length and on off. Elgar blocks it out towards cover.
Fuller, on leg. Elgar leans forward and defends it to the leg side.
Keegan Petersen walks in at number 3.

OUT! LBW! Aiden Markram slips under pressure this time and it is the Lord Thakur who finds the breakthrough for India. It is really hard to keep him out of the wickets with the form he is in. A full-length ball, on off, nips in a touch. Aiden Markram presses forward and looks to defend it out but misses to get hit on the pads. Shardul Thakur appeals again but this the umpire agrees and raises his dreaded finger. Aiden Markram starts walking away straightaway and does not even think about taking the review. It was plumb. Breakthrough for India early in the final session.
Commentary.Howout: lbw b Shardul Thakur

Commentary.Commentary: Swing and a miss! Markram looks all over the place here. Full length and outside off. Markram looks to drive it away but misses and Rishabh Pant collects it low and on his left.

Length ball, on the pads. Markram looks to flick it away but misses and gets hit on the pads. Shardul Thakur pleads yet again but the umpire shakes his head. It was clearly going down leg and hence KL Rahul does not take the review.

BEATEN! Fuller and outside off, nipping in a bit. Markram prods and looks to defend it out but misses and gets hit high on the pads. Shardul Thakur appeals but the umpire is unmoved. KL Rahul thinks it is going above the stumps.
FOUR! Powerful hit! Length ball, outside off. Markram stays on the back foot and punches it through point to find a boundary.
Fuller, on leg. Elgar stays back and flicks it through mid-wicket for just a single.
Good length, around middle and leg. Elgar flicks it towards square leg for a single. South Africa need 198 more runs to win.
A single this time! Good length, outside off. Markram pushes it to covers with soft hands and gets across for a single.
Full length, angled into the batter. Markram defends it back to the bowler with a straight bat.
Length ball, on the stumps. Markram gets squared up and defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller, on the pads. Markram flicks it to deep mid-wicket and collects a brace comfortably. The runs are coming easily now.
Full length, outside off. Markram defends it out solidly. There are three men in the slips for Markram.
Jasprit Bumrah to start from the other end.
Full length, on off. Elgar squeezes it out towards the man at gully.
Length, on the pads, Elgar flicks it towards deep square leg for a brace.
Make it three dots in a row now! Nicely bowled. Quicker, on a length, around off. Elgar works it towards the slip cordon off the outer half.
Two dots in a row! Good length, angled down leg. Elgar looks to flick it away but fails to get any bat on it.
Good length, on off. Elgar defends it to cover off the outer half.
Runs straightaway for South Africa in the final session. Length ball, sliding down leg. Elgar helps it around the corner towards fine leg. The batters run two comfortably.

We are all set for the final session of Day 3! Indian players stride out to the middle. Dean Elgar and Aiden Markram also jog out to resume their innings. Shardul Thakur to start with the ball for India.
... DAY 3, SESSION 3 …

Markram and Elgar scored runs at a brisk rate for the hosts. Bumrah and Shami were operating from each end. Both the bowlers got some movement off the deck but not enough to find the outside edge. This is the time when South African batter can make a statement with the blade here. They need to take it session by session, rather than charging towards the target. India, on the flip side, would hope to pick up a couple of wickets before the Stumps on Day 3 to put their noses in front. Do join us at 1830 IST (1300 GMT) to find out how things unravel in the final session.

South Africa have started the chase positively and have made sure to remain unscathed till the Tea break. India lacked in putting any pressure with the ball and would hope to change it in the final session.

FOUR! That's an edge but it doesn't carry and goes through the slip corridor for a boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram defends it with soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball falls short of the second slip fielder and sneaks through the gap for a boundary. South Africa are 34/0 at Tea on Day 3. They need 206 runs more to win this second Test match.
On a length, outside off. Aiden Markram lets it go this time.
This one stays low! A good-length delivery on middle. Aiden Markram watchfully defends it off the bottom of his blade towards the on side. A change of blade for Aiden Markram.
Back of a length, on off. Elgar defends this off the inside half of his blade towards the on side. A single taken.
He goes fuller this time around off. Elgar could have driven that but he decides to leave it alone.
Back of a length on middle. Elgar looks to defend but gets hit on the ribs.
A length ball, on off. Aiden Markram defends this solidly towards mid on. Aiden Markram is looking quite comfortable now.
Shami goes fuller on middle. Aiden Markram pushes it to mid on this time.
On a length on off. Aiden Markram solidly defends this towards the off side.
A good-length delivery outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.

FOUR! Glorious shot from Aiden Markram! A length ball on off. Aiden Markram plants his front foot forward and drives it crisply through covers for a lovely boundary. He is a sweet timer of the ball and he showed all of it in that shot.
Full and down the leg side this time. Aiden Markram looks to flick it but misses.
A length ball, on off. Elgar defends this solidly off the front foot. He gets this in the gap towards mid off and comes back for two runs.
On a length, on off. Aiden Markram solidly defends it towards covers and gets a quick single.
Bumrah goes fuller outside off. Elgar pushes this square on the off side and gets a single.
Another good-length delivery outside off. Elgar leaves it alone again.
A good-length delivery outside off. Elgar lets it go this time.

FOUR! Elgar was not in total control of that but he has picked up the boundary! A good-length delivery angling away from the batter. Elgar pushes forward to defend and gets a thick outside edge. The ball flies through gully and Elgar gets a boundary.
A good-length delivery outside off. Aiden Markram plants his front foot forward and lets it go. Aiden Markram is showing good foot movement so far.
A good-length delivery outside off. It seams away as Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
Shami pulls his length back a little and bowls this on off. Elgar pushes it to covers and takes a quick single.
Shami bowls this around off on a good length. Elgar leaves it alone as it seams away.
Shami goes outside off this time and bowls this on a length. Elgar leaves it comfortably.
A length ball and angling into middle. Elgar clips it to square leg.
A short ball to end the over on middle. Aiden Markram ducks under it.
FOUR! Aiden Markram is dealing in boundaries at the moment. A length ball on middle and leg. Aiden Markram clips it through mid-wicket for another boundary. He is a fine player when he gets going.
On a length, on off. Aiden Markram solidly blocks it towards the off side.
Good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone carefully.
Bumrah targets the stumps this time but end up drifting down the leg side. Aiden Markram looks to flick it but misses. Pant stops it with a good dive to his left.
On a good length outside off. Aiden Markram lets it go. Too wide to make him play there.
Shami drifts on the pads again. Aiden Markram clips it past square leg. Vihari runs behind it and cuts it off. Three runs taken.
FOUR! Aiden Markram gets his second boundary now. A length ball on middle. Aiden Markram leans forward and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary. Good shot.
In that corridor of uncertainity around off. Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
On middle and leg. A length ball and Aiden Markram works it to mid-wicket.
This time it is angled on middle. Elgar works it to fine leg for a single.
On a good length outside off. Elgar leaves it alone.
Mohammed Shami to steam in from the other end.

FOUR! A thick outside edge this time and that gives Aiden Markram and South Africa a boundary. A good-length delivery around off. Aiden Markram pushes forward to defend with soft hands and gets a thick outside edge. The ball goes through backward point for a boundary.
Another delivery on good-length with that away shape, Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
He is getting good away shape here. Bowls this on a good length outside off. Aiden Markram carefully leaves it.
On a good length and slightly wider outside off. Aiden Markram leaves it watchfully.
Another delivery in that channel around off. Aiden Markram shoulders his arms again.
Bumrah starts with a good-length delivery outside off. It seams away sharply as Aiden Markram leaves it alone.
